WEBVTT

00:00:00.820 --> 00:00:10.680
Alif Lam Meem, Allah, La ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hibb Al-Qayyum,

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:18.180
Nazala alayka Al-Kitab Bil-Haqq Musabdiqa Lima Bayna Yadihi Wa Anzala Al-Tawrat Wa Al-Injeel,

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:22.260
Min Qabnu Hudan Li Al-Nas Wa Anzala Al-Furqan,

00:00:22.260 --> 00:00:27.540
Inna Allatheena Kaffaru Bi Ayat Allahi Lahum Adabuhu Shadeed,

00:00:27.540 --> 00:00:31.420
Wa Allahu Azizun Muthu Muthiqan,

00:00:31.660 --> 00:00:36.380
Inna Allaha La Yakhda Alayhi Shajajin Fi Al-Ardi Wa La Fi Al-Sama,

00:00:36.380 --> 00:00:39.380
Bismillahir Rahmanir Raheem, Alhamdulillahi Rabbil Alameen,

00:00:39.380 --> 00:00:42.660
Wa Salatu Wa Salamu Al-Ataman Al-Akmalani,

00:00:42.660 --> 00:00:45.260
Ala Khayri Khalqihi Ajma'ina Wa Ba'id,

00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:49.020
All praises due to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:00:49.020 --> 00:00:52.980
Complete blessings and salutations be upon the Masterpiece,

00:00:52.980 --> 00:00:55.580
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:00:55.580 --> 00:00:58.020
And his entire household and all his companions,

00:00:58.020 --> 00:01:00.180
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them all,

00:01:00.220 --> 00:01:02.980
May Allah grant them goodness and mercy,

00:01:02.980 --> 00:01:04.980
And may Allah bless every single one of us,

00:01:04.980 --> 00:01:07.220
And grant us mercy as well,

00:01:07.220 --> 00:01:09.860
Beloved brothers and sisters in Islam,

00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:14.860
Do we realize that already seven days have gone by,

00:01:15.900 --> 00:01:18.460
Or should I say the Friday we started,

00:01:18.460 --> 00:01:21.060
This is another Friday, subhanallah,

00:01:21.060 --> 00:01:23.580
Before we know it, Ramadan will come to an end,

00:01:23.580 --> 00:01:26.780
Let's make use of this month before it leaves,

00:01:26.780 --> 00:01:29.500
Or before we leave it,

00:01:29.500 --> 00:01:31.980
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness,

00:01:31.980 --> 00:01:33.740
It's either we see the end of Ramadan,

00:01:33.740 --> 00:01:36.780
Or we are ended before the end of Ramadan,

00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:39.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us forgiveness,

00:01:39.300 --> 00:01:41.420
And may he make us conscious of the fact,

00:01:41.420 --> 00:01:43.300
That he is in absolute control,

00:01:43.300 --> 00:01:45.060
Yesterday I remember making mention,

00:01:45.060 --> 00:01:47.140
The story of Utbah ibn Rabi'ah,

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:49.580
And I'm sure a lot of us went home,

00:01:49.580 --> 00:01:50.740
And we looked at Surahs,

00:01:50.740 --> 00:01:51.580
Surah Fussilah,

00:01:51.580 --> 00:01:53.620
One person actually got hold of me,

00:01:53.620 --> 00:01:54.580
Messaged me and told me,

00:01:54.580 --> 00:01:55.420
Do you know what,

00:01:55.420 --> 00:01:57.700
I realized in the English Quran that I have,

00:01:57.700 --> 00:01:59.340
A page is actually missing,

00:01:59.340 --> 00:02:01.700
So I want to get back to the printers and so on,

00:02:01.700 --> 00:02:03.220
And I would not have realized it,

00:02:03.220 --> 00:02:04.900
Had it not been for this Surah,

00:02:04.900 --> 00:02:05.940
That you told us to check,

00:02:05.940 --> 00:02:07.220
So that was a good sign,

00:02:07.220 --> 00:02:08.980
To say people have been checking,

00:02:08.980 --> 00:02:11.420
Because it's very important for us to be plugged in,

00:02:11.420 --> 00:02:14.300
For your information this evening,

00:02:14.300 --> 00:02:15.420
The verses that we read,

00:02:15.420 --> 00:02:17.780
Of the Surahs that we did read this evening,

00:02:17.780 --> 00:02:19.540
They were connected to Quraysh,

00:02:19.540 --> 00:02:21.620
And the difficulties that were faced at the time,

00:02:21.620 --> 00:02:23.140
And just post Hijra,

00:02:23.140 --> 00:02:24.620
And the wars that took place,

00:02:24.620 --> 00:02:26.420
Wallahi touching verses,

00:02:26.420 --> 00:02:29.060
Insha'Allah we may mention a few of them this evening,

00:02:29.100 --> 00:02:32.740
But Utbah ibn Rabi'ah put his hand on the mouth of Muhammad,

00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:34.020
Salallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:02:34.020 --> 00:02:36.060
Because he did not want to hear the punishment,

00:02:36.060 --> 00:02:38.900
Because he knew that there were nations before them,

00:02:38.900 --> 00:02:39.940
Who were destroyed,

00:02:39.940 --> 00:02:42.820
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala not destroy us,

00:02:42.820 --> 00:02:44.340
We want to look at Abu Talib,

00:02:44.340 --> 00:02:46.300
This powerful man in Quraysh,

00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:47.900
Whom they feared a lot,

00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:49.260
He was not a Muslim,

00:02:49.260 --> 00:02:51.060
He was one of the elite of Quraysh,

00:02:51.060 --> 00:02:53.100
He had ignorance in him,

00:02:53.100 --> 00:02:54.740
To a very very high degree,

00:02:54.740 --> 00:02:56.420
But he was a very polite man,

00:02:56.460 --> 00:02:58.860
And he was very very disciplined,

00:02:58.860 --> 00:03:00.140
Cultured person,

00:03:00.140 --> 00:03:01.700
Although when I say ignorance,

00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:04.380
I mean he had some of his beliefs within him,

00:03:04.380 --> 00:03:06.180
That he just would not give up,

00:03:06.180 --> 00:03:08.060
So he did not accept the message of Muhammad,

00:03:08.060 --> 00:03:09.180
Salallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:03:09.180 --> 00:03:11.340
But there was a statement Muhammad,

00:03:11.340 --> 00:03:12.500
Salallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:03:12.500 --> 00:03:13.940
Made more than once,

00:03:13.940 --> 00:03:17.180
Some narrations say it was mentioned to Abu Talib,

00:03:17.180 --> 00:03:19.220
And some say not only Abu Talib,

00:03:19.220 --> 00:03:21.500
But even Utbah ibn Rabi'ah,

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:22.140
Where the Prophet,

00:03:22.140 --> 00:03:23.420
Salallahu alaihi wasallam said,

00:03:23.460 --> 00:03:26.500
Wallahi, if you were to put the sun in my right hand,

00:03:26.500 --> 00:03:28.140
And the moon in my left hand,

00:03:28.140 --> 00:03:31.700
And you were to tell me to leave what I am doing,

00:03:31.700 --> 00:03:35.580
What I am calling towards the belief in one Allah,

00:03:35.580 --> 00:03:36.820
I will not do that,

00:03:36.820 --> 00:03:38.220
I will not leave it,

00:03:38.220 --> 00:03:39.300
So Abu Talib told him,

00:03:39.300 --> 00:03:41.060
Okay, proceed and carry on,

00:03:41.060 --> 00:03:44.140
Don't worry, I will look after you as best as I can,

00:03:44.140 --> 00:03:45.660
And as for Utbah ibn Rabi'ah,

00:03:45.660 --> 00:03:46.580
He heard these verses,

00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:47.780
He went back to Quraysh,

00:03:47.780 --> 00:03:49.460
And I told you what he said,

00:03:49.460 --> 00:03:51.180
And he also did not accept,

00:03:51.180 --> 00:03:52.940
Which means there were people,

00:03:52.940 --> 00:03:54.740
Who knew what was right and wrong,

00:03:54.740 --> 00:03:56.460
As we mentioned yesterday,

00:03:56.460 --> 00:03:57.220
That Allah says,

00:04:15.060 --> 00:04:17.340
We know that it hurts you what they utter,

00:04:17.340 --> 00:04:19.300
We want to tell you they do not belay you,

00:04:19.300 --> 00:04:20.940
They don't deny the message,

00:04:20.940 --> 00:04:22.380
They are actually,

00:04:22.380 --> 00:04:25.180
Meaning in their hearts they know what is right,

00:04:25.180 --> 00:04:29.020
But they are disagreeing with you out of arrogance,

00:04:29.020 --> 00:04:30.100
They just don't want it,

00:04:30.100 --> 00:04:32.300
Because they are too proud and haughty,

00:04:32.300 --> 00:04:35.100
May Allah never make our pride such,

00:04:35.100 --> 00:04:37.700
That we do not come to the true path,

00:04:37.700 --> 00:04:41.660
Sometimes a person has a level in society or wealth,

00:04:41.660 --> 00:04:44.620
Or certain prestige that Allah has given them,

00:04:44.620 --> 00:04:45.780
And because of that,

00:04:45.780 --> 00:04:47.860
They don't want to come down to what is right,

00:04:47.860 --> 00:04:50.300
They cannot be told by ulama,

00:04:50.300 --> 00:04:51.780
They want to make all the decisions,

00:04:51.780 --> 00:04:52.900
And call all the shots,

00:04:52.900 --> 00:04:54.380
Because of who they are,

00:04:54.380 --> 00:04:58.300
They don't want to surrender to the law of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:04:58.300 --> 00:05:00.300
May Allah not make us from amongst those,

00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:02.620
That was a habit of the mushrik of Makkah,

00:05:02.620 --> 00:05:05.740
And Allah mentions this in the Quran,

00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:07.060
In more than one place,

00:05:07.060 --> 00:05:09.660
So now Abu Talib was a man,

00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:11.980
Who was looking after Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:05:11.980 --> 00:05:14.220
Because of him they couldn't touch him,

00:05:14.220 --> 00:05:16.580
They couldn't touch Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:05:16.580 --> 00:05:18.700
So the kuffar got together,

00:05:18.700 --> 00:05:20.460
And they decided let's have another chat,

00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:22.220
With Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:05:22.220 --> 00:05:24.260
They spoke to him and said okay,

00:05:24.260 --> 00:05:26.100
Let's arrive at a compromise,

00:05:26.100 --> 00:05:28.180
They saw his numbers were growing,

00:05:28.180 --> 00:05:31.980
No one who accepted his message turned back,

00:05:31.980 --> 00:05:34.300
But there were people from amongst them,

00:05:34.300 --> 00:05:37.260
Whom they were losing to Islam so to speak,

00:05:37.260 --> 00:05:38.860
So they said let's strike this deal,

00:05:38.860 --> 00:05:40.420
Agreement, what's the agreement?

00:05:40.420 --> 00:05:42.220
One day you worship our gods,

00:05:42.220 --> 00:05:43.980
One day we worship your god,

00:05:43.980 --> 00:05:45.500
Deal, one-one,

00:05:45.500 --> 00:05:46.580
Allahu Akbar,

00:05:46.580 --> 00:05:47.980
This is no football match,

00:05:47.980 --> 00:05:48.740
Allahu Akbar,

00:05:48.740 --> 00:05:51.340
Allah protect us, grant us goodness,

00:05:51.340 --> 00:05:53.300
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:05:53.300 --> 00:05:55.940
Immediately was given verses by Allah,

00:06:05.580 --> 00:06:07.780
Say oh disbelievers,

00:06:07.780 --> 00:06:11.100
I do not worship what you people believe in,

00:06:11.100 --> 00:06:13.340
And you do not worship what I believe in,

00:06:13.340 --> 00:06:15.260
And I don't worship what you believe in,

00:06:15.260 --> 00:06:17.380
And you do not worship what I believe in,

00:06:17.380 --> 00:06:18.620
For you is your faith,

00:06:18.620 --> 00:06:20.420
You can carry on doing what you want,

00:06:20.420 --> 00:06:21.660
And for me is my faith,

00:06:21.660 --> 00:06:23.060
Let me do what I have to,

00:06:23.060 --> 00:06:23.940
Allahu Akbar,

00:06:23.940 --> 00:06:25.060
What a law,

00:06:25.060 --> 00:06:25.700
What a law,

00:06:25.700 --> 00:06:26.940
Live and let live,

00:06:26.940 --> 00:06:27.900
That's the Quran,

00:06:30.820 --> 00:06:31.900
You have your faith,

00:06:31.900 --> 00:06:32.780
You can continue,

00:06:32.780 --> 00:06:33.820
You can go ahead,

00:06:33.820 --> 00:06:34.740
I have my faith,

00:06:34.740 --> 00:06:35.580
Subhanallah,

00:06:35.580 --> 00:06:36.420
Let me carry on,

00:06:36.420 --> 00:06:37.820
Let me worship Allah,

00:06:37.820 --> 00:06:40.060
And this is why we have this policy,

00:06:40.060 --> 00:06:41.620
The live and let live policy,

00:06:41.620 --> 00:06:43.980
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness,

00:06:43.980 --> 00:06:45.580
And may he give us a deep understanding,

00:06:45.580 --> 00:06:48.060
So now we know why that Surah was revealed,

00:06:48.060 --> 00:06:50.500
Because the Kuffar of Quraish wanted,

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:51.460
One day you worship,

00:06:51.460 --> 00:06:52.300
One day we worship,

00:06:52.300 --> 00:06:53.340
We come together,

00:06:53.340 --> 00:06:54.740
Wallahi in Malawi,

00:06:54.740 --> 00:06:57.260
And I visited this place a few times,

00:06:57.260 --> 00:07:00.460
There was a place that was a church,

00:07:00.460 --> 00:07:02.220
Where they used to call in the Muslims,

00:07:02.220 --> 00:07:03.260
Have Salah in it,

00:07:03.260 --> 00:07:04.260
And at the same time,

00:07:04.260 --> 00:07:06.540
They would have the church services as well,

00:07:06.540 --> 00:07:07.420
And they would say,

00:07:07.420 --> 00:07:07.900
Don't worry,

00:07:07.900 --> 00:07:09.060
We worship Allah as well,

00:07:09.060 --> 00:07:10.980
And you must come and worship here as well,

00:07:10.980 --> 00:07:12.540
Confusing the masses and the people,

00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:14.740
So that their deen is left,

00:07:14.780 --> 00:07:16.300
Until Allahu Akbar,

00:07:16.300 --> 00:07:18.540
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us,

00:07:18.540 --> 00:07:19.620
People went out there,

00:07:19.620 --> 00:07:21.660
And tried to explain to the people,

00:07:21.660 --> 00:07:22.420
Remember,

00:07:22.420 --> 00:07:24.420
The gift you have of Iman,

00:07:24.420 --> 00:07:25.820
It is so sweet,

00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:27.140
That we are taught,

00:07:27.140 --> 00:07:29.580
If the kings of the globe who are non-Muslim,

00:07:29.580 --> 00:07:31.620
Knew the sweetness we were in,

00:07:31.620 --> 00:07:34.140
They would fight us in order to get the sweetness,

00:07:34.140 --> 00:07:37.220
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us halawatul Iman,

00:07:37.220 --> 00:07:39.940
The belief in the one Maker who has made you,

00:07:39.940 --> 00:07:42.020
The one whom you are going to return to,

00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:42.900
That belief,

00:07:42.900 --> 00:07:44.260
The singular belief,

00:07:44.300 --> 00:07:46.140
Has so much sweetness in it,

00:07:46.140 --> 00:07:47.700
It is actually tasted,

00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:48.380
And thereafter,

00:07:48.380 --> 00:07:50.580
There is nothing that one would like to do,

00:07:50.580 --> 00:07:52.340
Besides to worship his own Maker,

00:07:52.340 --> 00:07:55.100
Never render an act of worship for anyone,

00:07:55.100 --> 00:07:55.860
Or anything,

00:07:55.860 --> 00:07:58.420
Besides Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:07:58.420 --> 00:07:59.900
So,

00:07:59.900 --> 00:08:01.660
Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:08:01.660 --> 00:08:03.340
Had uttered these verses to them,

00:08:03.340 --> 00:08:05.140
They were quiet once again,

00:08:05.140 --> 00:08:07.260
And now Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:10.220
Admonishes Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:08:10.220 --> 00:08:12.380
Literally scolds him,

00:08:12.380 --> 00:08:14.220
And these verses are so powerful,

00:08:14.220 --> 00:08:15.780
We read them every other day,

00:08:15.780 --> 00:08:17.420
Our children read them mashallah,

00:08:17.420 --> 00:08:19.060
We memorize these verses,

00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:20.140
What happened?

00:08:20.140 --> 00:08:23.140
The kuffar of Quraysh had called Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:08:23.140 --> 00:08:24.420
To discuss a matter,

00:08:24.420 --> 00:08:29.420
And he whilst he was talking with some of these seniors of Quraysh,

00:08:29.420 --> 00:08:32.300
Abdullah ibn Ummi Maktum radiallahu anhu,

00:08:32.300 --> 00:08:35.100
Who was a companion, a sahabi who had accepted Islam,

00:08:35.100 --> 00:08:36.460
He was blind,

00:08:36.460 --> 00:08:38.140
And he walked past,

00:08:38.140 --> 00:08:39.940
And he being blind,

00:08:39.940 --> 00:08:42.340
Wouldn't have known exactly what was going on,

00:08:42.380 --> 00:08:42.840
And he says,

00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:45.620
Ya Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:08:45.620 --> 00:08:47.100
Give me from the goodness,

00:08:47.100 --> 00:08:49.820
Tell me some of the goodness that Allah has given you,

00:08:49.820 --> 00:08:51.300
And Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:08:51.300 --> 00:08:53.340
Was busy talking to these kuffar,

00:08:53.340 --> 00:08:54.860
So he looked back,

00:08:54.860 --> 00:08:56.460
And he frowned at him a little bit,

00:08:56.460 --> 00:08:58.580
And carried on speaking with these people,

00:08:58.580 --> 00:08:59.660
Thinking that you know,

00:08:59.660 --> 00:09:02.420
These people might listen to what I have to say now,

00:09:02.420 --> 00:09:05.020
And if I am going to speak to this man right now,

00:09:05.020 --> 00:09:08.780
Then perhaps the message might be lost from these people here,

00:09:08.780 --> 00:09:10.980
And immediately Jibreel alayhi salatu wasalam,

00:09:10.980 --> 00:09:14.900
Came down with verses scolding Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:09:16.900 --> 00:09:18.580
He frowned and turned away,

00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:22.900
When the blind man came to him,

00:09:26.900 --> 00:09:29.140
And how do you know perhaps that blind man

00:09:29.140 --> 00:09:31.100
Would have been purified by your words,

00:09:31.100 --> 00:09:33.700
If you had turned to him and given him a few words,

00:09:37.780 --> 00:09:39.380
Or had he been reminded,

00:09:39.460 --> 00:09:40.740
It may have benefited him,

00:09:40.740 --> 00:09:43.420
The reminder would have benefited the blind man,

00:09:48.780 --> 00:09:51.700
As for those who are not even bothered about you,

00:09:51.700 --> 00:09:53.740
They are totally independent from you,

00:09:53.740 --> 00:09:54.780
They haven't asked you,

00:09:54.780 --> 00:09:56.300
You are telling them,

00:09:56.300 --> 00:09:58.900
You are concentrating on them so much,

00:10:01.180 --> 00:10:03.380
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala is telling him,

00:10:03.380 --> 00:10:05.420
The one who is calling you here,

00:10:05.420 --> 00:10:06.820
You didn't turn to him,

00:10:06.820 --> 00:10:10.020
And the one whom nothing is really going to benefit,

00:10:10.020 --> 00:10:12.620
You are spending your time with them so much,

00:10:12.620 --> 00:10:16.820
At the expense of these,

00:10:22.940 --> 00:10:25.620
And if they do not cleanse themselves,

00:10:25.620 --> 00:10:26.620
Purify themselves,

00:10:26.620 --> 00:10:27.740
It's not against you,

00:10:27.740 --> 00:10:29.140
Yours is the message,

00:10:29.140 --> 00:10:31.580
Now Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:10:31.580 --> 00:10:35.580
Immediately turned to Abdullah ibn Umme Maktum radiallahu anh,

00:10:35.620 --> 00:10:39.340
And even though he is a sahabi who was blind,

00:10:39.340 --> 00:10:41.420
He was always smiled too,

00:10:41.420 --> 00:10:43.580
And after that he always used to say,

00:10:43.580 --> 00:10:44.620
Ya Abdullah,

00:10:44.620 --> 00:10:47.900
You are the one whom Allah has admonished me about,

00:10:47.900 --> 00:10:49.740
Now one might wonder,

00:10:49.740 --> 00:10:51.580
The kuffar of Quraysh knew these verses,

00:10:51.580 --> 00:10:55.180
They knew that Allah admonished Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:10:55.180 --> 00:10:58.300
And from this you would know that these verses cannot be from him,

00:10:58.300 --> 00:11:02.820
Because who would want to have a scolding written in verses,

00:11:02.820 --> 00:11:03.900
Which they have brought,

00:11:03.900 --> 00:11:05.020
Allahu Akbar,

00:11:05.020 --> 00:11:06.660
And then we might ask,

00:11:06.660 --> 00:11:09.420
If this was a perfect example in the messenger,

00:11:09.420 --> 00:11:13.540
What benefit is there for me and you to read that he was scolded,

00:11:13.540 --> 00:11:14.660
Allahu Akbar,

00:11:14.660 --> 00:11:16.540
The answer is very simple,

00:11:16.540 --> 00:11:19.220
You see we have to follow his example in everything,

00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:20.300
So much so,

00:11:20.300 --> 00:11:22.620
His example is so complete,

00:11:22.620 --> 00:11:25.100
That for us who think we are so intelligent,

00:11:25.100 --> 00:11:26.780
And so well educated,

00:11:26.780 --> 00:11:28.540
Whenever we are corrected,

00:11:28.540 --> 00:11:30.460
How do we react to correction,

00:11:30.460 --> 00:11:32.940
We learn it from Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:11:32.980 --> 00:11:35.100
When he was corrected he didn't get angry,

00:11:35.100 --> 00:11:35.980
He didn't deny,

00:11:35.980 --> 00:11:37.060
He didn't delete,

00:11:37.060 --> 00:11:38.020
What he did is,

00:11:38.020 --> 00:11:38.820
He acknowledged,

00:11:38.820 --> 00:11:40.140
Immediately he surrendered,

00:11:40.140 --> 00:11:41.300
He changed himself,

00:11:41.300 --> 00:11:45.740
How many of us are ready to change ourselves whenever we are corrected,

00:11:45.740 --> 00:11:46.420
How many,

00:11:46.420 --> 00:11:47.580
We feel bad,

00:11:47.580 --> 00:11:50.180
Sometimes in Salah the Imam is corrected,

00:11:50.180 --> 00:11:51.500
And he feels so bad,

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:53.380
He stops talking to the man who corrected him,

00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:54.140
It happens,

00:11:54.140 --> 00:11:56.940
And sometimes what happens in society and community,

00:11:56.940 --> 00:11:57.860
Someone comes to us,

00:11:57.860 --> 00:11:58.420
Uncle,

00:11:58.420 --> 00:11:59.500
Please don't do this,

00:11:59.500 --> 00:12:00.900
Or they come to an aunt and say,

00:12:00.900 --> 00:12:01.580
You know what,

00:12:01.580 --> 00:12:02.900
My sister this is wrong,

00:12:02.900 --> 00:12:04.140
And we say who are you,

00:12:04.140 --> 00:12:05.020
Who are you,

00:12:05.020 --> 00:12:05.820
To tell me,

00:12:05.820 --> 00:12:06.900
Allahu Akbar,

00:12:06.900 --> 00:12:08.980
If you follow the perfect example,

00:12:08.980 --> 00:12:10.420
In that perfect example,

00:12:10.420 --> 00:12:12.140
Part of its perfection,

00:12:12.140 --> 00:12:13.740
Is to have in it,

00:12:13.740 --> 00:12:15.740
How to react when you are corrected,

00:12:15.740 --> 00:12:17.700
No matter how perfect you think you are,

00:12:17.700 --> 00:12:18.620
None of us are perfect,

00:12:18.620 --> 00:12:19.420
Subhanallah,

00:12:19.420 --> 00:12:21.020
So this is the beautiful verse,

00:12:21.020 --> 00:12:24.780
And these are the beautiful verses of Surat Abbas,

00:12:24.780 --> 00:12:27.220
And we know now when we read Abbas wa Tawalla,

00:12:27.220 --> 00:12:29.060
We will think of that blind man,

00:12:29.060 --> 00:12:32.140
Whom Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasalam was admonished about,

00:12:32.180 --> 00:12:33.860
Now the kuffar of Quraish,

00:12:33.860 --> 00:12:35.780
They came to Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:12:35.780 --> 00:12:36.140
And told him,

00:12:36.140 --> 00:12:36.380
Okay,

00:12:36.380 --> 00:12:38.020
We're ready to accept your message,

00:12:38.020 --> 00:12:41.500
On condition that you bring for us a sign,

00:12:41.500 --> 00:12:43.220
We want several signs from you,

00:12:43.220 --> 00:12:43.540
In fact,

00:12:43.540 --> 00:12:44.740
First they asked for one,

00:12:44.740 --> 00:12:45.780
What was the sign?

00:12:45.780 --> 00:12:46.540
They said,

00:12:46.540 --> 00:12:47.500
Something impossible,

00:12:47.500 --> 00:12:50.300
We want you to split the moon for us,

00:12:50.300 --> 00:12:52.580
We want you to split the moon,

00:12:52.580 --> 00:12:54.780
So Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:12:54.780 --> 00:12:57.140
Made dua to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:12:57.140 --> 00:12:58.460
As they looked,

00:12:58.460 --> 00:12:59.740
He pointed at the moon,

00:12:59.740 --> 00:13:00.980
Split it into two,

00:13:00.980 --> 00:13:03.060
The moon was split into two,

00:13:20.860 --> 00:13:22.220
The time has come near,

00:13:22.220 --> 00:13:23.460
The hour has come near,

00:13:23.460 --> 00:13:25.420
The moon has split asunder,

00:13:25.420 --> 00:13:28.980
The moon has been made into two parts,

00:13:28.980 --> 00:13:30.060
They saw it,

00:13:30.060 --> 00:13:31.300
And when they saw it,

00:13:31.300 --> 00:13:33.820
And they saw the sign that they had asked for,

00:13:33.820 --> 00:13:34.700
They said,

00:13:34.700 --> 00:13:36.660
This is indeed magic,

00:13:36.660 --> 00:13:37.660
Nothing but magic,

00:13:37.660 --> 00:13:39.100
But you asked for the sign,

00:13:39.100 --> 00:13:39.900
Here's the sign,

00:13:39.900 --> 00:13:40.740
It has come,

00:13:40.740 --> 00:13:42.180
And now you are telling us,

00:13:42.180 --> 00:13:44.940
That the moon being split is only magic,

00:13:44.940 --> 00:13:46.580
You are conning our eyes,

00:13:46.580 --> 00:13:48.580
We will notice subhanallah,

00:13:48.580 --> 00:13:50.260
That moon came back,

00:13:50.260 --> 00:13:51.860
By the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:13:51.860 --> 00:13:53.420
But to this day,

00:13:53.420 --> 00:13:55.180
There is a crack in the moon,

00:13:55.180 --> 00:13:56.420
Crater in the moon,

00:13:56.420 --> 00:13:58.540
If you take a look at the diagrams,

00:13:58.980 --> 00:14:02.420
The various photographic evidence there is,

00:14:02.420 --> 00:14:03.100
From the moon,

00:14:03.100 --> 00:14:04.660
You will find it up to now,

00:14:04.660 --> 00:14:08.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a deep understanding,

00:14:08.300 --> 00:14:10.420
And may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors,

00:14:10.420 --> 00:14:11.060
For us,

00:14:11.060 --> 00:14:12.700
That was a miracle that definitely happened,

00:14:12.700 --> 00:14:13.860
Mentioned in the Quran,

00:14:13.860 --> 00:14:16.260
And we have scientific evidence to back it up,

00:14:16.260 --> 00:14:17.860
And to prove that it did occur,

00:14:17.860 --> 00:14:18.820
Subhanallah,

00:14:18.820 --> 00:14:20.060
The kuffar of Quraysh,

00:14:20.060 --> 00:14:21.180
They derejected it,

00:14:21.180 --> 00:14:23.020
They said another sign we want,

00:14:29.540 --> 00:14:32.020
When they saw that now this one worked,

00:14:32.020 --> 00:14:33.380
And we still don't want to believe,

00:14:33.380 --> 00:14:34.100
They said okay,

00:14:34.100 --> 00:14:38.100
We're not going to believe in you until from the earth,

00:14:38.100 --> 00:14:41.100
You make springs gush wherever we want,

00:14:51.500 --> 00:14:53.780
Or we want you to see,

00:14:53.780 --> 00:14:55.580
Or we want to see with you,

00:14:55.580 --> 00:14:59.780
Gardens of dates and various other fruits and so on,

00:14:59.780 --> 00:15:02.660
And we want the rivers to flow,

00:15:02.660 --> 00:15:05.020
And to gush out in those gardens,

00:15:05.020 --> 00:15:05.740
Bring the gardens,

00:15:05.740 --> 00:15:06.860
Let's see what they are,

00:15:06.860 --> 00:15:09.140
And then those are the signs we want,

00:15:16.180 --> 00:15:18.020
We want to see you having a house,

00:15:18.020 --> 00:15:20.980
Made full of adornments and jewelry and so on,

00:15:20.980 --> 00:15:24.100
Or we want you to go right up into the heavens,

00:15:24.100 --> 00:15:25.100
Whilst we are watching,

00:15:25.140 --> 00:15:25.940
So you climb up,

00:15:25.940 --> 00:15:27.380
Let's see what happens,

00:15:27.380 --> 00:15:29.380
You say you're getting a revelation from the heavens,

00:15:29.380 --> 00:15:29.780
Go up,

00:15:29.780 --> 00:15:31.100
We want to watch it,

00:15:31.100 --> 00:15:32.220
And then they say,

00:15:35.060 --> 00:15:36.540
They knew that that could happen,

00:15:36.540 --> 00:15:37.340
If Allah wanted it,

00:15:37.340 --> 00:15:38.340
It can happen,

00:15:38.340 --> 00:15:39.180
So they said,

00:15:39.180 --> 00:15:40.340
And even if you climb up,

00:15:40.340 --> 00:15:41.540
We're not going to believe,

00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:49.500
Until you come back to us with a book that we can read,

00:15:49.500 --> 00:15:51.420
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:15:51.420 --> 00:15:55.380
Tell them O Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:16:04.340 --> 00:16:06.540
Glory be to my Lord,

00:16:06.540 --> 00:16:10.540
I am only but a human being as a messenger unto you,

00:16:10.540 --> 00:16:12.460
Stop asking me all these things,

00:16:12.460 --> 00:16:14.060
And this was a gift of Allah,

00:16:14.060 --> 00:16:16.780
Because if Quraish had been given these miracles,

00:16:16.780 --> 00:16:18.420
They would have been destroyed,

00:16:18.420 --> 00:16:21.500
But Allah had written Iman in the hearts of some of them,

00:16:21.500 --> 00:16:25.100
Or should I say the bulk of them who accepted Iman and Islam,

00:16:25.100 --> 00:16:25.860
Later on,

00:16:25.860 --> 00:16:27.580
A few years down the line,

00:16:27.580 --> 00:16:29.260
Allah had had mercy on them,

00:16:29.260 --> 00:16:31.260
So Allah kept them,

00:16:31.260 --> 00:16:36.060
There were just a handful of them who were destroyed before the victory of Makkah,

00:16:36.060 --> 00:16:36.980
But the bulk of them,

00:16:36.980 --> 00:16:37.780
Victory of Makkah,

00:16:37.780 --> 00:16:39.260
They all accepted Islam,

00:16:39.260 --> 00:16:42.100
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us an opening,

00:16:42.100 --> 00:16:45.580
And may He make us from amongst those who surrender,

00:16:45.580 --> 00:16:47.140
This evening we read a verse,

00:16:47.180 --> 00:16:48.420
And I want to repeat this verse,

00:16:48.420 --> 00:16:56.220
Because it is also one of the verses that is making mention of what the Kuffar of Quraish had asked Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:16:56.220 --> 00:16:57.420
You see how foolish,

00:16:57.420 --> 00:17:01.300
If a person comes to us and tells us,

00:17:01.300 --> 00:17:02.620
I am a messenger and so on,

00:17:02.620 --> 00:17:04.260
If we were there at the time,

00:17:04.260 --> 00:17:05.180
Perhaps we would have said,

00:17:05.180 --> 00:17:06.140
Okay,

00:17:06.140 --> 00:17:07.620
Bring for us some miracle,

00:17:07.620 --> 00:17:08.700
When the miracle came,

00:17:08.700 --> 00:17:10.540
We would have asked for something good,

00:17:10.540 --> 00:17:11.620
Do you know what they did?

00:17:11.620 --> 00:17:12.980
The Kuffar of Quraish,

00:17:12.980 --> 00:17:14.220
They says,

00:17:14.220 --> 00:17:20.220
وَإِذْ قَالُواْ اللَّهُمَّ إِنْ كَانَ هَذَا هُوَ الْحَقَّ مِنْ عِنْدِكَ

00:17:20.220 --> 00:17:24.860
فَأَمْطِلْ عَلَيْنَا حِجَارَةً مِنَ السَّمَاءَ

00:17:24.860 --> 00:17:29.140
أوِ اِتِنَا بِعَذَابٍ أَلِيمٍ

00:17:29.140 --> 00:17:29.660
They said,

00:17:29.660 --> 00:17:32.860
If this is the truth,

00:17:32.860 --> 00:17:34.380
Then O Allah,

00:17:34.380 --> 00:17:36.780
The Allah that is being called upon,

00:17:36.780 --> 00:17:38.980
Send down upon us,

00:17:38.980 --> 00:17:42.140
Stones from heaven to punish us,

00:17:42.180 --> 00:17:44.820
Rain, stones from heaven so we can be destroyed,

00:17:44.820 --> 00:17:46.380
Let's see,

00:17:46.380 --> 00:17:47.340
How foolish,

00:17:47.340 --> 00:17:48.100
If they said,

00:17:48.100 --> 00:17:49.020
Send us gold,

00:17:49.020 --> 00:17:50.620
Perhaps they would have got gold,

00:17:50.620 --> 00:17:52.220
Send us some silver, some jewelry,

00:17:52.220 --> 00:17:53.060
It would have come,

00:17:53.060 --> 00:17:53.660
But they saying,

00:17:53.660 --> 00:17:55.660
Send us stones to punish us,

00:17:55.660 --> 00:17:56.940
So Allah says,

00:17:56.940 --> 00:18:02.340
وَمَا كَانَ اللَّهُ لِي وَعَذِّبَهُمْ وَأَنْتَ فِيهِمْ

00:18:02.340 --> 00:18:03.500
Allah will not punish them

00:18:03.500 --> 00:18:05.020
Whilst you are in their midst,

00:18:05.020 --> 00:18:06.420
Subhanallah,

00:18:06.420 --> 00:18:08.300
Allah will not punish them

00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:10.060
Whilst you are in their midst,

00:18:10.060 --> 00:18:11.700
O Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam,

00:18:11.700 --> 00:18:13.540
Because the message is still fresh,

00:18:13.540 --> 00:18:14.420
It's carrying on,

00:18:14.420 --> 00:18:16.260
There will still be people who are going to turn,

00:18:16.260 --> 00:18:18.740
We're not going to destroy all of them,

00:18:18.740 --> 00:18:19.900
Subhanallah,

00:18:19.900 --> 00:18:20.940
And the verses continue,

00:18:20.940 --> 00:18:22.700
So these are just some of the verses

00:18:22.700 --> 00:18:25.940
That had been made mention of at that particular time,

00:18:25.940 --> 00:18:28.100
What was going on.

00:18:28.100 --> 00:18:29.900
Then the persecution continued,

00:18:29.900 --> 00:18:31.580
And it continued more and more,

00:18:31.580 --> 00:18:33.980
So much so that the Prophet Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:18:33.980 --> 00:18:35.860
Gathered those who had believed and told them,

00:18:35.860 --> 00:18:36.700
You know what,

00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:39.180
I allow you now to leave Makkah if you would like,

00:18:39.180 --> 00:18:41.100
Go to Habashah which is Abyssinia,

00:18:41.100 --> 00:18:42.260
You will find a man there,

00:18:42.260 --> 00:18:43.820
The Negus of Abyssinia,

00:18:43.820 --> 00:18:45.220
His name was Ashamah,

00:18:45.220 --> 00:18:47.340
And he is a just ruler,

00:18:47.340 --> 00:18:48.420
He will not punish you,

00:18:48.420 --> 00:18:49.500
He will be very just,

00:18:49.500 --> 00:18:50.460
He will look after you,

00:18:50.460 --> 00:18:52.060
Explain to him what has happened,

00:18:52.060 --> 00:18:53.260
And proceed.

00:18:53.260 --> 00:18:55.340
So because of the persecutions,

00:18:55.340 --> 00:18:57.420
A group from amongst them proceeded,

00:18:57.420 --> 00:18:59.860
The first group who left Makkah

00:18:59.860 --> 00:19:01.100
Because of persecutions,

00:19:01.100 --> 00:19:01.980
Imagine,

00:19:01.980 --> 00:19:04.300
Those who left Makkah the first time,

00:19:04.300 --> 00:19:05.500
None of them were slaves,

00:19:05.500 --> 00:19:07.540
They were all from top families,

00:19:07.540 --> 00:19:09.340
They were all people

00:19:09.380 --> 00:19:11.700
Who were children of wealthy,

00:19:11.700 --> 00:19:14.380
Influential people in Quraysh,

00:19:14.380 --> 00:19:15.900
And they decided to go,

00:19:15.900 --> 00:19:17.940
Them and their wives at times,

00:19:17.940 --> 00:19:19.780
Because they were not babies,

00:19:19.780 --> 00:19:22.140
But they were adults,

00:19:22.140 --> 00:19:23.060
And at the same time,

00:19:23.060 --> 00:19:25.300
Children of people who were leaders,

00:19:25.300 --> 00:19:27.180
So there were 10 men,

00:19:27.180 --> 00:19:28.860
According to the most correct narrations,

00:19:28.860 --> 00:19:31.100
Although some take it to 12,

00:19:31.100 --> 00:19:32.460
And four men,

00:19:32.460 --> 00:19:34.020
According to the most correct narration,

00:19:34.020 --> 00:19:35.300
Some people say five,

00:19:35.300 --> 00:19:36.140
Whatever it was,

00:19:36.140 --> 00:19:37.340
It's a similar figure,

00:19:37.340 --> 00:19:39.260
They had left and it is reported,

00:19:39.260 --> 00:19:41.100
Ibn Hisham makes mention of the fact,

00:19:41.100 --> 00:19:44.260
That Uthman ibn Mad'un was made their leader,

00:19:44.260 --> 00:19:46.820
They left towards the sea,

00:19:46.820 --> 00:19:49.500
And Quraysh began their journey behind them,

00:19:49.500 --> 00:19:50.460
They sent some people,

00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:52.300
Go and track these people down,

00:19:52.300 --> 00:19:54.860
But Quraysh did not manage to even go,

00:19:54.860 --> 00:19:56.740
Anywhere near before they could get there,

00:19:56.740 --> 00:19:58.180
These people were on their boat,

00:19:58.180 --> 00:19:59.500
And they were on the way,

00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:01.580
And they had arrived then in Abyssinia,

00:20:01.580 --> 00:20:03.540
And they remained there for a little period of time,

00:20:03.540 --> 00:20:05.620
From amongst them was Mus'ab ibn Umayr,

00:20:05.620 --> 00:20:06.860
Radhiallahu anhu,

00:20:06.860 --> 00:20:07.980
And from amongst them was

00:20:07.980 --> 00:20:09.020
Uthman ibn Affan,

00:20:09.020 --> 00:20:10.420
Radhiallahu anhu,

00:20:10.420 --> 00:20:11.980
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:20:11.980 --> 00:20:13.700
To grant us goodness,

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:16.060
So they had gone,

00:20:16.060 --> 00:20:16.980
When they went,

00:20:16.980 --> 00:20:19.420
Here in Makkatul Mukarrama,

00:20:19.420 --> 00:20:22.620
Something very very powerful happened,

00:20:22.620 --> 00:20:25.380
What happened?

00:20:25.380 --> 00:20:27.220
The Prophet salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:20:27.220 --> 00:20:31.220
One day was near the Kaaba,

00:20:31.220 --> 00:20:34.500
And one narration says close to Safa,

00:20:34.500 --> 00:20:35.860
So being close to Safa,

00:20:35.860 --> 00:20:37.580
Which is also not too far from the Kaaba,

00:20:37.580 --> 00:20:38.620
He was worshipping Allah,

00:20:38.620 --> 00:20:39.860
And Abu Jahl came to him,

00:20:39.900 --> 00:20:42.620
And beat him up and swore him,

00:20:42.620 --> 00:20:44.500
And now as I told you,

00:20:44.500 --> 00:20:47.140
Family members would always stand up,

00:20:47.140 --> 00:20:49.820
At that time no one really noticed,

00:20:49.820 --> 00:20:51.580
But Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib,

00:20:51.580 --> 00:20:57.220
Was the uncle of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam,

00:20:57.220 --> 00:20:58.780
He was out hunting,

00:20:58.780 --> 00:21:01.180
When he got back from his journey from hunting,

00:21:01.180 --> 00:21:02.020
Someone told him,

00:21:02.020 --> 00:21:03.860
Do you know what Abu Jahl did to your nephew?

00:21:03.860 --> 00:21:05.380
Gave him a good hiding,

00:21:05.380 --> 00:21:08.580
He made him bleed according to one narration,

00:21:08.580 --> 00:21:10.700
And another narration says he swore him,

00:21:10.700 --> 00:21:12.780
Whatever it was, he was abused,

00:21:12.780 --> 00:21:17.220
So Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib went with his bow and arrow,

00:21:17.220 --> 00:21:19.180
And he struck Abu Jahl,

00:21:19.180 --> 00:21:19.780
And he says,

00:21:19.780 --> 00:21:24.300
أَتَشْتُمُهُ وَأَنَ عَلَى دِينِهِ أَقُولُ مَا يَقُولُ

00:21:24.300 --> 00:21:25.660
That was a powerful statement,

00:21:25.660 --> 00:21:26.860
The people were shocked,

00:21:26.860 --> 00:21:28.580
They used to sit around the Kaaba,

00:21:28.580 --> 00:21:30.300
Waiting and listening and talking,

00:21:30.300 --> 00:21:33.340
They had little groups and cliques that they used to sit around,

00:21:33.340 --> 00:21:35.900
And they heard Hamza saying,

00:21:35.900 --> 00:21:38.660
Are you abusing this nephew of mine,

00:21:38.660 --> 00:21:40.460
When I follow his religion,

00:21:40.460 --> 00:21:43.460
And I say exactly what he says,

00:21:43.460 --> 00:21:44.860
Subhanallah,

00:21:44.860 --> 00:21:49.020
That was the first declaration of Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib,

00:21:49.020 --> 00:21:51.220
The Muslims became so happy,

00:21:51.220 --> 00:21:54.540
They were so happy because he was a powerful man,

00:21:54.540 --> 00:21:55.780
And this was a victory,

00:21:55.780 --> 00:21:56.740
So look,

00:21:56.740 --> 00:22:00.860
One of the victories granted by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:22:00.860 --> 00:22:05.140
After the occasion of the abuse of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:22:05.140 --> 00:22:06.180
By Abu Jahl,

00:22:06.180 --> 00:22:08.900
Who was one of the arch enemies of Islam,

00:22:08.900 --> 00:22:10.580
This is why we always say,

00:22:10.580 --> 00:22:12.220
رُبَّ ضَارَّةِ النَافِعَةِ

00:22:12.220 --> 00:22:13.580
Today we read a verse,

00:22:13.580 --> 00:22:16.860
وَيَمْكُرُونَ وَيَمْكُرُ اللَّهُ

00:22:16.860 --> 00:22:19.420
وَاللَّهُ خَيْرٌ مَا كِرِينَ

00:22:19.420 --> 00:22:20.300
They plot,

00:22:20.300 --> 00:22:21.820
And Allah plans and plots,

00:22:21.820 --> 00:22:24.220
And Allah is the best of planners and plotters,

00:22:24.220 --> 00:22:28.700
You will never ever be able to plot against Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:22:28.700 --> 00:22:29.860
He always wins.

00:22:29.860 --> 00:22:31.580
So now what has happened?

00:22:31.580 --> 00:22:33.300
Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib,

00:22:33.300 --> 00:22:34.540
He used to start,

00:22:34.540 --> 00:22:36.820
Meaning he went to Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:22:36.860 --> 00:22:39.260
And he started learning the religion,

00:22:39.260 --> 00:22:40.740
Let's listen very carefully,

00:22:40.740 --> 00:22:42.540
He started learning this religion,

00:22:42.540 --> 00:22:45.940
And they used to gather in the house of Al-Arqam ibn Abu Al-Arqam,

00:22:45.940 --> 00:22:47.340
Who was a Mahzoumi,

00:22:47.340 --> 00:22:49.140
And the clan of Mahzoum,

00:22:49.140 --> 00:22:52.220
They had a bit of a problem with these Banu Hashim,

00:22:52.220 --> 00:22:54.660
They had a bit of a problem with these people,

00:22:54.660 --> 00:22:56.460
And what they did is,

00:22:56.460 --> 00:23:01.380
They had set the flag of war at one stage against them,

00:23:01.380 --> 00:23:05.140
So Banu Hashim was a little bit worried whenever it came to Banu Mahzoum,

00:23:05.180 --> 00:23:07.540
And they would never ever imagine,

00:23:07.540 --> 00:23:10.900
That a person from Banu Mahzoum who was only in his teens,

00:23:10.900 --> 00:23:14.820
Would have accepted this faith and opened his doors for them to come in,

00:23:14.820 --> 00:23:18.100
They quietly used to go to the house of Al-Arqam ibn Abu Al-Arqam,

00:23:18.100 --> 00:23:20.620
Very silently learned this religion.

00:23:20.620 --> 00:23:22.380
For your information to this day,

00:23:22.380 --> 00:23:24.940
There are some countries where Muslims are persecuted,

00:23:24.940 --> 00:23:28.540
They cannot learn their deen unless they do so privately,

00:23:28.540 --> 00:23:30.780
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness,

00:23:30.780 --> 00:23:34.660
Some of these countries are ruled by Muslims,

00:23:34.660 --> 00:23:39.060
So-called Muslims, may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala save us.

00:23:39.060 --> 00:23:42.260
So this was happening at the time of Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:23:42.260 --> 00:23:47.060
And Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wa sallam realized that this is the power of Allah,

00:23:47.060 --> 00:23:49.060
We are starting to grow in number,

00:23:49.060 --> 00:23:50.340
And he made a dua,

00:23:50.340 --> 00:23:54.020
He says Allahumma a'izzal Islam bi ahadil umarain,

00:23:54.020 --> 00:23:59.220
O Allah, grant strength to Islam by the acceptance of Islam,

00:23:59.220 --> 00:24:01.140
Of some of these powerful people,

00:24:01.140 --> 00:24:02.460
One of the two Umars,

00:24:02.460 --> 00:24:04.340
One known as Umar ibn Al-Khattab,

00:24:04.340 --> 00:24:06.340
The other one known as Amr ibn Hisham,

00:24:06.340 --> 00:24:08.300
The enemy of Allah,

00:24:08.300 --> 00:24:11.620
Imagine he had just abused Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:24:11.620 --> 00:24:13.100
And now the hands are coming up to say,

00:24:13.100 --> 00:24:15.540
O Allah, this man is so strong,

00:24:15.540 --> 00:24:19.780
If this energy and this strength was used in the right direction,

00:24:19.780 --> 00:24:23.500
It would come to so much good use,

00:24:23.500 --> 00:24:26.020
But because it is being used in the bad direction,

00:24:26.020 --> 00:24:27.860
Look at the quality of leadership,

00:24:27.860 --> 00:24:30.180
A leader is he who looks at his enemies,

00:24:30.180 --> 00:24:32.060
And sees the power of the enemies,

00:24:32.060 --> 00:24:33.340
And thinks to himself,

00:24:33.340 --> 00:24:36.980
If we can get all this power to be used on our side,

00:24:36.980 --> 00:24:39.220
We perhaps would become a force to be reckoned with,

00:24:39.220 --> 00:24:40.060
Subhanallah,

00:24:40.060 --> 00:24:42.140
This was Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:24:42.140 --> 00:24:42.820
He says O Allah,

00:24:42.820 --> 00:24:45.140
If that man who is doing so much harm,

00:24:45.140 --> 00:24:46.940
He's so powerful, they fear him,

00:24:46.940 --> 00:24:48.620
If he can come into Islam,

00:24:48.620 --> 00:24:49.820
Imagine what would happen,

00:24:49.820 --> 00:24:51.740
So many people would accept Islam,

00:24:51.740 --> 00:24:53.500
Sometimes my brothers and sisters,

00:24:53.500 --> 00:24:55.500
Allah has put you in a position,

00:24:55.500 --> 00:24:57.540
That if you start dressing properly,

00:24:57.540 --> 00:24:59.700
Another 30-40 people start dressing properly,

00:24:59.700 --> 00:25:00.580
They're watching you,

00:25:00.580 --> 00:25:01.820
You're like the role model,

00:25:02.380 --> 00:25:03.300
The queen of teens,

00:25:03.300 --> 00:25:04.300
Allah protect us,

00:25:04.300 --> 00:25:05.340
They're all watching you,

00:25:05.340 --> 00:25:06.620
You wear this, they wear that,

00:25:06.620 --> 00:25:07.900
You wear that, they wear this,

00:25:07.900 --> 00:25:10.500
So why don't we seize this opportunity?

00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:12.020
Abu Jahal did not,

00:25:12.020 --> 00:25:14.500
And Abu Jahal would not,

00:25:14.500 --> 00:25:17.220
But when it came to Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a,

00:25:17.220 --> 00:25:18.340
Listen to what happened,

00:25:18.340 --> 00:25:19.620
He came out one morning,

00:25:19.620 --> 00:25:20.820
He was fed up,

00:25:20.820 --> 00:25:22.940
Every day I'm hearing the same story,

00:25:22.940 --> 00:25:24.220
This man causing problems,

00:25:24.220 --> 00:25:25.300
He's swearing our gods,

00:25:25.300 --> 00:25:27.060
He's saying don't worship the idols,

00:25:27.060 --> 00:25:30.700
He wants to divert us from the religion of our forefathers,

00:25:30.740 --> 00:25:32.940
How can I allow this to continue,

00:25:32.940 --> 00:25:34.140
I'm a strong man,

00:25:34.140 --> 00:25:35.500
I am ibn Al-Khattab,

00:25:35.500 --> 00:25:38.340
Let me go out and finish him once and for all.

00:25:38.340 --> 00:25:40.460
He had similar thinking to that of Abu Jahal,

00:25:40.460 --> 00:25:41.580
But they feared him,

00:25:41.580 --> 00:25:44.060
Because he was much more powerful

00:25:44.060 --> 00:25:45.820
In terms of physical strength,

00:25:45.820 --> 00:25:48.820
Omar ibn Al-Khattab r.a was a solid man,

00:25:48.820 --> 00:25:51.020
No one dare tread his path,

00:25:51.020 --> 00:25:52.100
Cross his path,

00:25:53.300 --> 00:25:54.940
So as he came out with his sword,

00:25:54.940 --> 00:25:56.300
And you could see the intent,

00:25:56.300 --> 00:25:57.740
When a man comes out of his home,

00:25:57.740 --> 00:25:59.180
It was not so big,

00:25:59.180 --> 00:26:00.620
It was a small area,

00:26:00.620 --> 00:26:02.540
But he walked out of his home with his sword,

00:26:02.540 --> 00:26:05.140
And he was met by one of the sahabah r.a,

00:26:05.140 --> 00:26:06.500
Where are you going?

00:26:06.500 --> 00:26:09.340
He says I'm going to sort Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam out,

00:26:09.340 --> 00:26:10.180
Want to kill him off,

00:26:10.180 --> 00:26:10.900
That's it,

00:26:10.900 --> 00:26:11.260
Finish,

00:26:11.260 --> 00:26:13.900
We won't have a problem after today in Quraysh,

00:26:13.900 --> 00:26:15.340
The problem will be sorted,

00:26:15.340 --> 00:26:17.540
So this man thought to himself,

00:26:17.540 --> 00:26:20.020
Let me give this man a piece of advice,

00:26:20.020 --> 00:26:21.740
You want to start there,

00:26:21.740 --> 00:26:22.980
Start with your family,

00:26:22.980 --> 00:26:25.420
Do you know your sister Fatima bint Al-Khattab,

00:26:25.420 --> 00:26:26.860
She has accepted Islam,

00:26:26.860 --> 00:26:28.060
She is following him,

00:26:28.060 --> 00:26:29.220
Why don't you start with her?

00:26:29.220 --> 00:26:30.260
He says good idea,

00:26:30.300 --> 00:26:32.340
And he started walking in the direction of,

00:26:32.340 --> 00:26:33.900
His brother-in-law's place,

00:26:33.900 --> 00:26:35.220
Saeed bint Zubair,

00:26:35.220 --> 00:26:38.100
Saeed bint Zayid,

00:26:38.100 --> 00:26:41.180
Who was married to his sister Fatima bint Al-Khattab,

00:26:41.180 --> 00:26:43.660
And he knocks on the door,

00:26:43.660 --> 00:26:45.540
They had according to one narration,

00:26:45.540 --> 00:26:48.260
They were learning some Quran from a little parchment,

00:26:48.260 --> 00:26:49.300
That they had had,

00:26:49.300 --> 00:26:50.260
Because as we know,

00:26:50.260 --> 00:26:51.820
There was no paper at the time,

00:26:51.820 --> 00:26:54.260
But they used to write on skins and little logs,

00:26:54.260 --> 00:26:56.620
And little pieces of wood and parchments and so on,

00:26:56.620 --> 00:26:58.180
And they had a little bit of this,

00:26:58.180 --> 00:26:59.980
And they were learning it according to one narration,

00:27:00.020 --> 00:27:01.900
Khabbab bint Al-Arad was teaching them,

00:27:01.900 --> 00:27:03.660
And what happened is,

00:27:03.660 --> 00:27:04.740
They were indoors,

00:27:04.740 --> 00:27:06.500
They heard this bang on the door,

00:27:06.500 --> 00:27:08.300
They immediately hid Khabbab,

00:27:08.300 --> 00:27:08.900
Go and hide,

00:27:08.900 --> 00:27:09.740
You're not supposed to be here,

00:27:09.740 --> 00:27:11.740
What are you doing here?

00:27:11.740 --> 00:27:13.300
And when they opened the door,

00:27:13.300 --> 00:27:15.380
They hid those pages as well,

00:27:15.380 --> 00:27:18.140
He came in and started beating them up,

00:27:18.140 --> 00:27:19.100
Immediately,

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:19.900
Started beating them,

00:27:19.900 --> 00:27:21.260
How can you accept Muhammad,

00:27:21.260 --> 00:27:23.020
You must disbelieve in Muhammad,

00:27:23.020 --> 00:27:24.260
You must this, you are that,

00:27:24.260 --> 00:27:25.740
You are traitors, you are tyrants,

00:27:25.740 --> 00:27:26.980
You have disgraced us,

00:27:26.980 --> 00:27:28.580
You are people like this and like that,

00:27:28.580 --> 00:27:29.580
My own family,

00:27:29.580 --> 00:27:30.980
And he's beating, beating,

00:27:30.980 --> 00:27:34.420
And suddenly his sister began to bleed,

00:27:34.420 --> 00:27:39.060
When that blood came on the hands of Umar ibn Al-Khattab r.a.,

00:27:39.060 --> 00:27:40.260
Something clicked,

00:27:40.260 --> 00:27:41.780
This is my sister man,

00:27:41.780 --> 00:27:43.180
I'm supposed to be looking after her,

00:27:43.180 --> 00:27:44.340
Here's her blood,

00:27:44.340 --> 00:27:46.100
How can this have happened?

00:27:46.100 --> 00:27:46.860
He says, okay,

00:27:46.860 --> 00:27:48.180
You know what,

00:27:48.180 --> 00:27:48.980
Pause for a moment,

00:27:48.980 --> 00:27:49.900
What were you people doing?

00:27:49.900 --> 00:27:51.500
I want to know,

00:27:51.500 --> 00:27:55.660
So they were trying to avoid the question and so on,

00:27:55.660 --> 00:27:56.940
And after his insistence,

00:27:56.940 --> 00:27:57.980
They said, okay,

00:27:57.980 --> 00:27:59.780
We were learning a few words

00:27:59.780 --> 00:28:03.380
From what Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam had brought,

00:28:03.380 --> 00:28:04.900
Now there was a rumor in Makkah,

00:28:04.900 --> 00:28:07.700
To say that Muhammad has come with a religion

00:28:07.700 --> 00:28:10.220
Where so many rules and regulations,

00:28:10.220 --> 00:28:13.300
He's telling you that women need to be dressed appropriately

00:28:13.300 --> 00:28:14.900
And you should respect your women,

00:28:14.900 --> 00:28:16.300
You cannot inherit women,

00:28:16.300 --> 00:28:18.020
They must be given inheritance,

00:28:18.020 --> 00:28:19.740
You need to do this, you need to do that,

00:28:19.740 --> 00:28:20.780
You are not allowed to do this,

00:28:20.780 --> 00:28:21.780
Not allowed to do that,

00:28:21.780 --> 00:28:23.340
So many rules and regulations,

00:28:23.340 --> 00:28:24.820
So it just makes life difficult,

00:28:24.820 --> 00:28:27.420
Islam is a religion that just makes life difficult,

00:28:27.420 --> 00:28:28.540
Up to today,

00:28:28.540 --> 00:28:30.260
There are Muslims who think

00:28:30.260 --> 00:28:32.700
That Islam has too many rules and regulations,

00:28:32.700 --> 00:28:34.180
So that's why it's difficult,

00:28:34.180 --> 00:28:35.220
It's not difficult,

00:28:35.220 --> 00:28:37.140
Listen to why Allah has done that,

00:28:37.140 --> 00:28:39.220
So Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu

00:28:39.220 --> 00:28:41.060
Was one of those who knew that rumor,

00:28:41.060 --> 00:28:43.180
And he looks at his sister,

00:28:43.180 --> 00:28:44.340
I want to see those pages,

00:28:44.340 --> 00:28:45.580
They said, look,

00:28:45.580 --> 00:28:47.780
You want to see what it is,

00:28:47.780 --> 00:28:49.180
You first need to cleanse,

00:28:49.180 --> 00:28:50.700
They made him cleanse,

00:28:50.700 --> 00:28:52.860
And they took out these pages,

00:28:52.860 --> 00:28:54.020
Do you know what,

00:28:54.020 --> 00:28:57.380
A man who came out to kill Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:28:58.340 --> 00:29:01.620
He saw these pages,

00:29:01.620 --> 00:29:06.220
He read not more than four verses,

00:29:06.220 --> 00:29:07.460
He began to cry,

00:29:07.460 --> 00:29:09.140
What were these verses,

00:29:09.140 --> 00:29:11.820
The opening verses of surah Taha,

00:29:11.820 --> 00:29:13.740
Taha

00:29:13.740 --> 00:29:21.260
Ma anzalna alayka al qur'an li tashqa

00:29:21.260 --> 00:29:27.020
Illa tathkiratan liman yakhsha

00:29:27.140 --> 00:29:32.620
Tanzeelan mimman khalaqal arda

00:29:32.620 --> 00:29:36.540
Wa as-samawati al ulaa

00:29:36.540 --> 00:29:37.940
Taha

00:29:37.940 --> 00:29:40.780
No one knows the meaning of those two letters,

00:29:40.780 --> 00:29:44.820
Indeed, your Lord has not revealed the Quran to you

00:29:44.820 --> 00:29:48.580
For it to be a source of your distress,

00:29:48.580 --> 00:29:52.900
It is only but a reminder for those who are truthful,

00:29:52.900 --> 00:29:54.100
For those who are humble,

00:29:54.100 --> 00:29:55.540
For those who are fearful,

00:29:55.580 --> 00:29:57.380
For those who have khashya in them,

00:29:57.380 --> 00:30:01.420
For those who have that sense of God consciousness in them,

00:30:01.420 --> 00:30:06.140
It is a revelation from the one who created the skies and the earth,

00:30:06.140 --> 00:30:09.180
Umar ibn Al-Khattab was moved already,

00:30:09.180 --> 00:30:11.380
He's never seen verses of this,

00:30:11.380 --> 00:30:15.340
It had the answer to a question that he had at the back of his mind,

00:30:15.340 --> 00:30:17.460
And at the same time his sister is there,

00:30:17.460 --> 00:30:18.860
These are pure verses,

00:30:18.860 --> 00:30:20.460
He senses the purity,

00:30:20.460 --> 00:30:22.660
Take me to Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:30:22.660 --> 00:30:24.660
I want to go to him,

00:30:24.700 --> 00:30:25.860
You want to go to him?

00:30:25.860 --> 00:30:28.100
Well, they noticed now softened heart,

00:30:28.100 --> 00:30:30.820
Immediately they took him to Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:30:30.820 --> 00:30:32.060
And as he walked,

00:30:32.060 --> 00:30:33.580
He was told to follow,

00:30:33.580 --> 00:30:36.820
He followed and they went out to whose house?

00:30:36.820 --> 00:30:40.700
Al-Arqam ibn Abi Al-Arqam radiallahu anhu,

00:30:40.700 --> 00:30:43.420
One of these maqzoom boys,

00:30:43.420 --> 00:30:44.740
And who was in the house?

00:30:44.740 --> 00:30:48.380
Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib was a senior person at the time,

00:30:48.380 --> 00:30:51.660
He was in this house as the uncle of Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:30:51.660 --> 00:30:54.620
He was the most powerful up to that time,

00:30:54.620 --> 00:30:57.220
So when this man came to the door,

00:30:57.220 --> 00:31:01.260
And the people saw that this man has come to the door,

00:31:01.260 --> 00:31:03.780
Of the house of Al-Arqam ibn Abi Al-Arqam,

00:31:03.780 --> 00:31:06.660
Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam is inside,

00:31:06.660 --> 00:31:08.980
They knew he had made a dua,

00:31:08.980 --> 00:31:10.420
That O Allah strengthen Islam,

00:31:10.420 --> 00:31:12.740
And they knew there's nothing impossible here,

00:31:12.740 --> 00:31:13.860
But they were worried,

00:31:13.860 --> 00:31:15.940
So Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib says,

00:31:15.940 --> 00:31:17.260
Let him in,

00:31:17.260 --> 00:31:18.340
This is Umar,

00:31:18.340 --> 00:31:24.940
...

00:31:24.940 --> 00:31:25.820
This is Umar,

00:31:25.820 --> 00:31:26.780
Let him come in,

00:31:26.780 --> 00:31:30.100
If Allah intends goodness from him,

00:31:30.100 --> 00:31:31.380
He will accept Islam,

00:31:31.380 --> 00:31:33.700
And if this man intends any harm,

00:31:33.700 --> 00:31:36.180
Ya Allah make it easy for us to overcome him,

00:31:36.180 --> 00:31:38.060
We can overcome him with his own sword,

00:31:38.060 --> 00:31:39.940
He had his sword,

00:31:39.940 --> 00:31:41.540
And as he came in,

00:31:41.540 --> 00:31:45.580
It is reported that the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam held his clothing,

00:31:45.580 --> 00:31:46.420
And held it and says,

00:31:47.300 --> 00:31:50.660
What brings you here?

00:31:50.660 --> 00:31:51.140
He says,

00:31:51.140 --> 00:31:56.820
...

00:31:56.820 --> 00:32:00.660
I have come to bear witness that there is none worthy of worship besides Allah,

00:32:00.660 --> 00:32:03.820
And that you are indeed the messenger of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:32:03.820 --> 00:32:04.900
Allahu Akbar,

00:32:04.900 --> 00:32:08.220
When they heard the messenger saying Allahu Akbar,

00:32:08.220 --> 00:32:11.260
They knew that Umar ibn Al-Khattab had entered the fold of Islam,

00:32:11.260 --> 00:32:13.100
They all began to say Allahu Akbar,

00:32:13.100 --> 00:32:14.780
I have a point I want to raise here,

00:32:14.780 --> 00:32:17.180
Umar ibn Al-Khattab was an enemy of Islam,

00:32:17.220 --> 00:32:20.420
He read a few verses of the Quran which changed his life,

00:32:20.420 --> 00:32:21.700
We are Muslims,

00:32:21.700 --> 00:32:23.700
We read the Quran cover to cover,

00:32:23.700 --> 00:32:25.060
Khatmah after khatmah,

00:32:25.060 --> 00:32:26.740
And still it has not moved us,

00:32:26.740 --> 00:32:27.340
Why?

00:32:27.340 --> 00:32:28.180
What is the problem?

00:32:28.180 --> 00:32:29.500
Allahu Akbar,

00:32:29.500 --> 00:32:30.100
What is the problem?

00:32:30.100 --> 00:32:32.060
Where are our hearts?

00:32:32.060 --> 00:32:36.620
One, two verses moved people who were mountains in enmity,

00:32:36.620 --> 00:32:38.820
And made them mountains of love,

00:32:38.820 --> 00:32:39.460
We,

00:32:39.460 --> 00:32:40.180
What has happened to us?

00:32:40.180 --> 00:32:40.900
We are Muslim,

00:32:40.900 --> 00:32:41.620
Come on,

00:32:41.620 --> 00:32:43.860
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala move us,

00:32:43.860 --> 00:32:45.780
We know and I know of kuffar,

00:32:45.780 --> 00:32:48.780
Just believers who have read the Quran and turned to Islam,

00:32:48.780 --> 00:32:50.820
And we know of Muslims who read the Quran,

00:32:50.820 --> 00:32:53.860
But still don't turn to the laws of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:32:53.860 --> 00:32:55.500
May Allah forgive our shortcomings,

00:32:55.500 --> 00:32:57.380
May He protect us from hypocrisy,

00:32:57.380 --> 00:32:59.220
May He give us a turning point,

00:32:59.220 --> 00:33:02.660
So this was the Islam of Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu,

00:33:02.660 --> 00:33:03.700
Rumor spread,

00:33:03.700 --> 00:33:04.460
Do you know what happened?

00:33:04.460 --> 00:33:08.380
One narration says Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu asks,

00:33:08.380 --> 00:33:13.940
Who is the person in Quraish who spreads rumors the fastest?

00:33:13.940 --> 00:33:15.260
Allahu Akbar,

00:33:15.260 --> 00:33:17.340
Imagine how brave this man is,

00:33:17.340 --> 00:33:18.500
Others didn't want to know,

00:33:18.500 --> 00:33:20.940
Didn't want the people to know they accepted Islam,

00:33:20.940 --> 00:33:23.540
Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu comes and says,

00:33:23.540 --> 00:33:28.540
Who is the man in Quraish who has a name of spreading gossip like wildfire?

00:33:28.540 --> 00:33:29.340
They gave him a name,

00:33:29.340 --> 00:33:31.540
Do you want to know the name?

00:33:31.540 --> 00:33:33.980
Jamil ibn Ma'mar Al-Jumahi,

00:33:33.980 --> 00:33:35.300
They say that man,

00:33:35.300 --> 00:33:36.500
So he went to Jamil,

00:33:36.500 --> 00:33:36.940
He tells him,

00:33:36.940 --> 00:33:38.420
You know what,

00:33:38.420 --> 00:33:40.940
I have accepted Islam and I am a Muslim,

00:33:40.940 --> 00:33:42.020
Jamil started running,

00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:42.780
Running where?

00:33:42.780 --> 00:33:44.140
He ran to the Kaaba,

00:33:44.180 --> 00:33:45.420
He stood on top,

00:33:45.420 --> 00:33:46.420
Right on one of the hillocks,

00:33:46.420 --> 00:33:46.620
He says,

00:33:46.620 --> 00:33:47.220
Hey,

00:33:47.220 --> 00:33:49.340
Ibn Al-Khattab has accepted Islam,

00:33:49.340 --> 00:33:52.380
He has renamed from the religion of our forefathers,

00:33:52.380 --> 00:33:53.780
And everyone was shocked,

00:33:53.780 --> 00:33:54.980
That's what Umar wanted,

00:33:54.980 --> 00:33:59.300
And on this side Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu tells Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:33:59.300 --> 00:34:00.500
According to one narration,

00:34:00.500 --> 00:34:02.980
He was the 40th person to accept Islam,

00:34:02.980 --> 00:34:04.500
According to one narration,

00:34:04.500 --> 00:34:05.860
And perhaps the 40th man,

00:34:05.860 --> 00:34:07.980
Allah knows best,

00:34:07.980 --> 00:34:08.340
He says,

00:34:08.340 --> 00:34:09.060
Oh messenger,

00:34:09.060 --> 00:34:10.220
Alasna ala al-haq,

00:34:10.220 --> 00:34:11.460
Aren't we on the right path?

00:34:11.460 --> 00:34:11.740
He says,

00:34:11.740 --> 00:34:12.900
Yes we are,

00:34:12.900 --> 00:34:13.140
He says,

00:34:13.140 --> 00:34:13.620
Okay,

00:34:13.620 --> 00:34:14.380
Let's get up,

00:34:14.380 --> 00:34:16.780
And we will read our Salah from today in the Haram,

00:34:16.780 --> 00:34:17.340
In a group,

00:34:17.340 --> 00:34:19.980
Why must we duck and dive and go to someone's house,

00:34:19.980 --> 00:34:21.380
And then we go to the Kaaba,

00:34:21.380 --> 00:34:22.100
Or singularly,

00:34:22.100 --> 00:34:24.100
And we want to go to this place in the outskirts,

00:34:24.100 --> 00:34:25.420
Let's go,

00:34:25.420 --> 00:34:26.940
Allahu Akbar,

00:34:26.940 --> 00:34:28.260
When the Prophet made a dua,

00:34:28.260 --> 00:34:28.700
Ya Allah,

00:34:28.700 --> 00:34:33.100
Strengthen Islam through the acceptance of Islam of one of these two people,

00:34:33.100 --> 00:34:35.740
The man came into the fold within moments,

00:34:35.740 --> 00:34:37.980
Within a short space of time,

00:34:37.980 --> 00:34:40.140
It is reported few days after Hamza,

00:34:40.140 --> 00:34:41.740
Ibn Abdul Muttalib radiallahu anhu,

00:34:41.740 --> 00:34:42.580
This happened,

00:34:42.620 --> 00:34:43.260
And when he came,

00:34:43.260 --> 00:34:44.460
Look at the strength,

00:34:44.460 --> 00:34:45.220
What happened,

00:34:45.220 --> 00:34:46.620
They made two lines of people,

00:34:46.620 --> 00:34:47.540
20 in this line,

00:34:47.540 --> 00:34:48.300
20 in the other,

00:34:48.300 --> 00:34:49.580
According to some narrations,

00:34:49.580 --> 00:34:51.420
Perhaps the figure might not be that accurate,

00:34:51.420 --> 00:34:55.580
But Hamza Ibn Abdul Muttalib was standing at the front of one of them,

00:34:55.580 --> 00:34:57.820
And Umar Ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu,

00:34:57.820 --> 00:34:58.940
The front of the other,

00:34:58.940 --> 00:35:02.380
They marched on to the Kaaba,

00:35:02.380 --> 00:35:03.500
The Kaaba,

00:35:03.500 --> 00:35:05.140
They went into this Haram,

00:35:05.140 --> 00:35:07.060
And remember that time it wasn't what it is today,

00:35:07.060 --> 00:35:08.060
It was just a Kaaba,

00:35:08.060 --> 00:35:09.300
And a little vicinity around,

00:35:09.300 --> 00:35:10.500
They used to sit around,

00:35:10.500 --> 00:35:12.140
Quraish used to sit in little groups,

00:35:12.140 --> 00:35:13.020
They used to talk,

00:35:13.020 --> 00:35:13.980
And they used to chat,

00:35:13.980 --> 00:35:15.940
This is why it's an insult for us,

00:35:15.940 --> 00:35:17.220
To come to the house of Allah,

00:35:17.220 --> 00:35:20.060
And have little groups inside or outside and chat,

00:35:20.060 --> 00:35:20.860
That's wrong,

00:35:20.860 --> 00:35:23.020
You come to the house of Allah not to chat,

00:35:23.020 --> 00:35:26.020
You come in order to worship Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:35:26.020 --> 00:35:27.740
It's about time we learned that,

00:35:27.740 --> 00:35:30.220
Yes, if you have something to say out of respect,

00:35:30.220 --> 00:35:33.540
But the Kuffar of Quraish used to use the vicinity of the Kaaba,

00:35:33.540 --> 00:35:34.620
To sit and chat,

00:35:34.620 --> 00:35:37.540
And to boast and to brag about what happened this day and that day,

00:35:37.540 --> 00:35:39.060
And sit and drink alcohol,

00:35:39.060 --> 00:35:41.500
We sit outside the masjid and smoke cigarettes,

00:35:42.260 --> 00:35:44.140
And we sit and chat up to late at night,

00:35:44.140 --> 00:35:47.020
And we were the ones who were complaining about two minutes early,

00:35:47.020 --> 00:35:48.500
That Taraweeh did not finish,

00:35:48.500 --> 00:35:51.460
So that's why now we're sitting outside for 20 minutes,

00:35:51.460 --> 00:35:52.340
Allah protect us,

00:35:52.340 --> 00:35:54.180
Where is our brains gone sometimes,

00:35:54.180 --> 00:35:56.500
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors,

00:35:56.500 --> 00:35:59.540
May He grant us a lesson from these mushrik of Makkah,

00:35:59.540 --> 00:36:02.220
And may He open really the doors of mercy upon us,

00:36:02.220 --> 00:36:03.500
And the doors of understanding,

00:36:03.500 --> 00:36:05.380
So these people were sitting,

00:36:05.380 --> 00:36:09.060
They witnessed Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu walk,

00:36:09.100 --> 00:36:10.540
They were looking at each other,

00:36:10.540 --> 00:36:11.820
They can't say anything,

00:36:11.820 --> 00:36:13.300
No words to utter,

00:36:13.300 --> 00:36:15.660
They seen Hamza ibn Abdul Muttalib,

00:36:15.660 --> 00:36:17.460
Rumor began to do its rounds,

00:36:17.460 --> 00:36:19.740
Soon news got to Habasha,

00:36:19.740 --> 00:36:20.940
News got to Abyssinia,

00:36:20.940 --> 00:36:23.020
The day the Muslims have accepted,

00:36:23.020 --> 00:36:26.300
Meaning the people of Quraish are starting to accept Islam,

00:36:26.300 --> 00:36:29.540
So these people started returning from Abyssinia,

00:36:29.540 --> 00:36:31.460
Three months they had just gone in,

00:36:31.460 --> 00:36:33.100
This was the first Hijra,

00:36:33.100 --> 00:36:35.260
The first migration to Abyssinia,

00:36:35.260 --> 00:36:37.500
Within three months they began to come back,

00:36:37.540 --> 00:36:39.780
Because they heard this rumour,

00:36:39.780 --> 00:36:42.220
That Quraish started accepting Islam,

00:36:42.220 --> 00:36:43.060
How did they hear it?

00:36:43.060 --> 00:36:46.540
They heard it because of the acceptance of some of these strong people,

00:36:46.540 --> 00:36:48.700
And they had gone because of persecution,

00:36:48.700 --> 00:36:51.340
Who wants to spend time away from their families,

00:36:51.340 --> 00:36:52.900
Away from where they grew up,

00:36:52.900 --> 00:36:55.340
Away from where they were born and so on,

00:36:55.340 --> 00:36:56.420
Subhanallah,

00:36:56.420 --> 00:36:58.020
So when they came back,

00:36:58.020 --> 00:37:01.340
They noticed they were not allowed to enter Makkah,

00:37:01.340 --> 00:37:03.300
Except one of two conditions,

00:37:03.300 --> 00:37:05.180
Either quietly hiding,

00:37:05.180 --> 00:37:06.060
They came in,

00:37:06.060 --> 00:37:08.020
No one knew,

00:37:08.020 --> 00:37:13.140
Or someone had to come and lay a guarantee,

00:37:13.140 --> 00:37:15.700
And this was common at the time of Rasulullah SAW,

00:37:15.700 --> 00:37:17.460
Even the pre-Islamic era,

00:37:17.460 --> 00:37:19.820
The guarantee,

00:37:19.820 --> 00:37:21.580
How it was is,

00:37:21.580 --> 00:37:23.980
A strong man from the people of Quraish,

00:37:23.980 --> 00:37:24.940
Would guarantee that,

00:37:24.940 --> 00:37:27.620
Look, this man let him come in on my guarantee,

00:37:27.620 --> 00:37:29.900
No harm do you,

00:37:29.900 --> 00:37:31.180
Meaning you should not harm him,

00:37:31.180 --> 00:37:33.380
And he will not engage in X, Y and Z,

00:37:33.380 --> 00:37:34.740
And that was like a guarantee,

00:37:34.740 --> 00:37:36.580
So some of them entered in that way,

00:37:36.580 --> 00:37:38.220
And some of them came quietly,

00:37:38.220 --> 00:37:42.410
But something else happened,

00:37:42.410 --> 00:37:44.050
These mushriks of Quraish,

00:37:44.050 --> 00:37:46.650
They decided we need to fix the Muslims,

00:37:46.650 --> 00:37:49.090
They're starting to become so powerful,

00:37:49.090 --> 00:37:53.210
So they decided to go to the Jewish clans around,

00:37:53.210 --> 00:37:54.490
Some of the Jewish people,

00:37:54.490 --> 00:37:55.290
And ask them,

00:37:55.290 --> 00:37:57.170
How do we deal with this man?

00:37:57.170 --> 00:37:59.530
So they said, very simple,

00:37:59.530 --> 00:38:02.210
If you want to know whether he is a prophet or not,

00:38:02.210 --> 00:38:03.650
You ask him three questions,

00:38:03.650 --> 00:38:05.850
If he can answer you, he's a prophet,

00:38:05.850 --> 00:38:08.690
If he cannot answer you, he's not a prophet,

00:38:08.690 --> 00:38:09.970
What are the three questions?

00:38:09.970 --> 00:38:11.890
They say the first,

00:38:11.890 --> 00:38:17.530
Ask him about some youth of a long time ago,

00:38:17.530 --> 00:38:18.490
What a question,

00:38:18.490 --> 00:38:19.210
Someone comes to you,

00:38:19.210 --> 00:38:22.930
Tell me about some youth of a long time ago,

00:38:22.930 --> 00:38:24.530
Second question,

00:38:24.530 --> 00:38:27.170
Ask him about a man who went,

00:38:27.170 --> 00:38:29.650
Who traveled from the east to the west,

00:38:29.650 --> 00:38:32.050
And he was powerful,

00:38:32.050 --> 00:38:35.170
A man of a long time ago,

00:38:35.170 --> 00:38:36.250
Ask him,

00:38:36.250 --> 00:38:37.330
What type of a question?

00:38:37.330 --> 00:38:38.450
The third question,

00:38:38.450 --> 00:38:41.890
Ask him about the soul and how it works,

00:38:41.890 --> 00:38:44.210
So the Quraish were excited,

00:38:44.210 --> 00:38:47.370
They thought this man is never going to come with an answer,

00:38:47.370 --> 00:38:49.090
They told Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:38:49.090 --> 00:38:50.410
We have three questions for you,

00:38:50.410 --> 00:38:52.010
You answer them, we accept,

00:38:52.010 --> 00:38:54.770
You don't answer them, don't accept,

00:38:54.770 --> 00:38:55.930
What are the questions?

00:38:55.930 --> 00:38:57.210
So when they said the questions,

00:38:57.210 --> 00:39:00.770
He said, I will give you the response tomorrow,

00:39:00.770 --> 00:39:02.850
And he went back waiting for revelation,

00:39:02.850 --> 00:39:04.730
Revelation did not come,

00:39:04.730 --> 00:39:05.610
They came, what happened?

00:39:05.610 --> 00:39:08.450
He said, tomorrow, revelation did not come,

00:39:08.450 --> 00:39:10.210
Tomorrow, revelation did not come,

00:39:10.210 --> 00:39:11.690
15 days went by,

00:39:11.690 --> 00:39:13.970
And Quraish came to him and told him,

00:39:13.970 --> 00:39:14.890
What is it?

00:39:14.890 --> 00:39:16.330
15 days have gone by,

00:39:16.330 --> 00:39:17.850
You haven't yet come,

00:39:17.850 --> 00:39:20.050
And Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam was saddened,

00:39:20.050 --> 00:39:21.290
He was making dua to Allah,

00:39:21.290 --> 00:39:24.450
Ya Allah send me revelation with the response,

00:39:24.450 --> 00:39:27.530
And 15 days later the revelation came down,

00:39:27.530 --> 00:39:29.530
Why did it delay?

00:39:29.530 --> 00:39:30.730
Simple reason,

00:39:30.730 --> 00:39:33.730
Because Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam did not say,

00:39:33.730 --> 00:39:35.250
Inshallah.

00:39:35.250 --> 00:39:37.410
So Allah says in Surah al-Kahf,

00:39:37.410 --> 00:39:50.690
ولا تقولن لشيء إني فاعل ذلك غدا إلا أن يشاء الله

00:39:50.690 --> 00:39:54.090
Don't ever say you are going to do something tomorrow,

00:39:54.090 --> 00:39:55.770
Without adding the statement,

00:39:55.770 --> 00:39:58.970
If Allah wills with it.

00:39:58.970 --> 00:39:59.850
So if you say,

00:39:59.850 --> 00:40:01.010
I'm going to do this tomorrow,

00:40:01.010 --> 00:40:01.890
Say, Inshallah,

00:40:01.890 --> 00:40:04.330
Which means if Allah wills,

00:40:04.330 --> 00:40:05.170
As they say,

00:40:05.170 --> 00:40:06.690
God willing in the English language,

00:40:06.690 --> 00:40:08.130
We say if Allah wills,

00:40:08.130 --> 00:40:10.570
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us that lesson.

00:40:10.570 --> 00:40:12.370
So when revelation came,

00:40:12.370 --> 00:40:14.850
The response of all three questions came,

00:40:14.850 --> 00:40:16.690
One was Surah al-Kahf,

00:40:16.690 --> 00:40:19.970
The whole Surah named after the people of the cave,

00:40:19.970 --> 00:40:23.870
Those were the youth of a long time ago,

00:40:23.870 --> 00:40:26.230
The seven of them according to some narrations,

00:40:26.230 --> 00:40:30.310
And Allah makes mention of it in Surah al-Kahf,

00:40:30.310 --> 00:40:36.430
إِنَّهُمْ فِتَّيَةٌ آمَنُوا بِرَبِّهِمْ وَزِدْنَاهُمْ هُدَاءٌ

00:40:36.430 --> 00:40:38.950
They were the youth who believed in their Rabb,

00:40:38.950 --> 00:40:41.150
And we increased them in guidance,

00:40:41.150 --> 00:40:42.710
And Allah gives the story,

00:40:42.710 --> 00:40:43.590
Beautiful story,

00:40:43.590 --> 00:40:44.470
Surah al-Kahf,

00:40:44.470 --> 00:40:47.910
We mentioned it last year when we spoke of the stories of the prophets,

00:40:47.910 --> 00:40:51.030
And when we spoke of the sleeper caves and so on,

00:40:51.030 --> 00:40:53.790
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a lesson.

00:40:53.790 --> 00:40:54.910
Secondly,

00:40:54.910 --> 00:40:57.790
The man who traveled from the east to the west,

00:40:57.790 --> 00:40:58.870
The powerful man,

00:40:58.870 --> 00:41:00.670
He was Dhul-Qarnayn,

00:41:00.670 --> 00:41:02.390
قَالُوا يَذَلْقَرْنَيْنِ

00:41:02.390 --> 00:41:04.990
Also in Surah al-Kahf towards the end,

00:41:04.990 --> 00:41:06.750
Where Allah makes mention of Dhul-Qarnayn,

00:41:06.750 --> 00:41:07.990
He traveled from here to there,

00:41:07.990 --> 00:41:08.790
This is what he did,

00:41:08.790 --> 00:41:09.870
And this is what happened,

00:41:09.870 --> 00:41:12.870
He had a meeting with Ya'juj and Ma'juj,

00:41:12.870 --> 00:41:15.910
Where he entrapped them and so on,

00:41:15.910 --> 00:41:17.990
So all this was made mention of,

00:41:17.990 --> 00:41:19.710
Quraysh was gobsmacked.

00:41:19.710 --> 00:41:22.660
The third question,

00:41:22.660 --> 00:41:25.700
وَيَسْأَلُونَكَ عَنِ الْرُوحِ

00:41:25.700 --> 00:41:28.660
قُلِ الْرُوحُ مِنْ أَمْلِ رَبِّهِ

00:41:28.660 --> 00:41:34.180
وَمَا أُوْتِيتُمْ مِنَ الْعِلْمِ إِلَّا قَلِيلًا

00:41:34.180 --> 00:41:37.900
They are asking you about the soul and how it operates,

00:41:37.900 --> 00:41:41.220
Tell them the soul is by the instruction of Allah,

00:41:41.220 --> 00:41:44.900
And He has not given you knowledge except but a little.

00:41:44.900 --> 00:41:49.100
That is exactly what the Jewish people found in their books,

00:41:49.100 --> 00:41:52.500
In terms of a response when it came to the soul.

00:41:52.500 --> 00:41:54.420
So they knew this man is a messenger,

00:41:54.420 --> 00:41:56.300
Still they did not accept.

00:41:56.300 --> 00:41:57.580
And the people of Quraysh,

00:41:57.620 --> 00:41:58.780
They still did not accept.

00:41:58.780 --> 00:41:59.700
Look at this,

00:41:59.700 --> 00:42:00.980
They asking questions,

00:42:00.980 --> 00:42:02.420
When the questions are answered,

00:42:02.420 --> 00:42:03.820
They still don't want to take it.

00:42:03.820 --> 00:42:08.020
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala not make us from those who break our promises.

00:42:08.020 --> 00:42:10.620
Now the kuffar of Makkah were left with one option,

00:42:10.620 --> 00:42:11.660
They went to Abu Talib,

00:42:11.660 --> 00:42:13.140
They said Abu Talib,

00:42:13.140 --> 00:42:14.340
Now it's too much,

00:42:14.340 --> 00:42:16.140
We need your nephew,

00:42:16.140 --> 00:42:17.940
You need to stop protecting him,

00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:19.860
And this guarantee of yours,

00:42:19.860 --> 00:42:21.340
You need to withdraw it.

00:42:21.340 --> 00:42:24.140
We are making you the following offer,

00:42:24.140 --> 00:42:27.740
We can give you blood money of how many people you want,

00:42:27.740 --> 00:42:28.820
Not just one,

00:42:28.820 --> 00:42:31.300
Give him to us, we execute him.

00:42:31.300 --> 00:42:33.300
He said no, I'm not interested.

00:42:33.300 --> 00:42:35.940
Imagine blood money is always one for one.

00:42:35.940 --> 00:42:38.300
They said we give you how many you like,

00:42:38.300 --> 00:42:41.900
Say it, you want blood money of 10 people we give you,

00:42:41.900 --> 00:42:43.220
But give us this one man,

00:42:43.220 --> 00:42:44.060
He said no.

00:42:45.620 --> 00:42:48.020
Then they said okay, we make you another offer,

00:42:48.020 --> 00:42:52.140
Take any one of our children from the highest of families,

00:42:52.140 --> 00:42:53.900
Give us your nephew.

00:42:53.900 --> 00:42:56.300
You can keep that child and give him to us.

00:42:56.300 --> 00:43:00.220
He says are you people mad, are you crazy?

00:43:00.220 --> 00:43:03.940
You want me to take one of your sons to look after him,

00:43:03.940 --> 00:43:05.580
So he can grow nicely,

00:43:05.580 --> 00:43:08.020
And you want to take my nephew in order to kill him,

00:43:08.020 --> 00:43:10.620
Doesn't make sense, not at all, foolish.

00:43:10.620 --> 00:43:12.460
He says I'm not going to agree with that.

00:43:12.460 --> 00:43:13.700
So then they said okay,

00:43:13.700 --> 00:43:16.060
We're not going to have any luck with this Abu Talib.

00:43:16.060 --> 00:43:17.580
Now they gathered,

00:43:17.580 --> 00:43:20.900
They gathered around and they decided amongst the tribes,

00:43:20.900 --> 00:43:22.780
Let us sign a document,

00:43:22.780 --> 00:43:26.620
We must sign a document as unlettered as they were,

00:43:26.620 --> 00:43:28.580
They decided to put pen on paper,

00:43:28.580 --> 00:43:30.580
In the sense they decided to write something.

00:43:30.580 --> 00:43:31.900
What did they write?

00:43:31.900 --> 00:43:34.660
They drew up a treaty to say,

00:43:34.660 --> 00:43:38.060
These families of Banu al-Muttalib and Banu Hashim,

00:43:38.060 --> 00:43:39.220
Who are Muslim,

00:43:39.220 --> 00:43:45.460
We are going to expel them from our cities,

00:43:45.460 --> 00:43:48.380
Meaning from our little suburb that we are living in right now,

00:43:48.380 --> 00:43:49.580
This part of Makkah,

00:43:49.580 --> 00:43:51.620
They can go out into the outskirts,

00:43:51.620 --> 00:43:54.980
And we will not deal with them,

00:43:54.980 --> 00:43:58.140
We will not buy from them and we will not sell to them,

00:43:58.140 --> 00:44:03.500
We will not marry in them and we will not allow them to marry in us,

00:44:03.500 --> 00:44:07.900
And we will not provide them anything and we won't accept anything from them,

00:44:07.900 --> 00:44:13.340
We will never sign treaties with them and we don't want them to sign anything with us,

00:44:13.340 --> 00:44:16.820
We will not mix with them and we don't want them to mix with us,

00:44:16.820 --> 00:44:20.060
We will not sit with them and we don't want them to sit with us,

00:44:20.060 --> 00:44:23.220
We will not talk to them and we don't want them to talk to us.

00:44:23.220 --> 00:44:27.180
We will not enter their houses and we don't want them to enter our houses.

00:44:27.180 --> 00:44:29.300
Complete sanctions.

00:44:29.300 --> 00:44:31.660
Imagine.

00:44:31.660 --> 00:44:33.220
Against who?

00:44:33.220 --> 00:44:34.940
Against believers.

00:44:34.940 --> 00:44:36.980
People who believed in one Allah.

00:44:36.980 --> 00:44:40.340
People who had the direct help of the Almighty.

00:44:40.340 --> 00:44:42.660
But this was all the plan of the Almighty.

00:44:42.660 --> 00:44:46.940
Later on, the Muslims always speak about how these days were.

00:44:46.940 --> 00:44:50.220
There were people who hated Islam at that particular time,

00:44:50.220 --> 00:44:52.620
who accepted it later on and they say,

00:44:52.620 --> 00:44:54.820
how foolish we were at that time.

00:44:54.820 --> 00:44:57.380
How Allah blessed us to hold us a little bit.

00:44:57.380 --> 00:45:01.140
Had Allah punished us whilst we were still in that time,

00:45:01.140 --> 00:45:03.020
we perhaps would have never ever believed.

00:45:03.020 --> 00:45:07.140
Now it's us and our offspring and children and children's children.

00:45:07.140 --> 00:45:08.820
May Allah grant us steadfastness.

00:45:08.820 --> 00:45:10.900
So this thing, they wrote it.

00:45:10.900 --> 00:45:12.300
And what did they do?

00:45:12.300 --> 00:45:15.540
They hung it in the Kaaba, inside the Kaaba.

00:45:15.540 --> 00:45:16.660
They hung it.

00:45:16.660 --> 00:45:19.020
And everyone abided by it.

00:45:19.020 --> 00:45:21.260
So no one spoke to these people.

00:45:21.260 --> 00:45:22.660
And what happened?

00:45:22.660 --> 00:45:26.540
Because they used to take Muhammad SAW to the outskirts

00:45:26.540 --> 00:45:30.140
in order to protect him from being killed by the people of Quraysh.

00:45:30.140 --> 00:45:32.940
Because had he been killed by the people of Quraysh,

00:45:32.940 --> 00:45:35.460
there would have been massive disaster there.

00:45:35.460 --> 00:45:38.140
There would have been an outbreak of war.

00:45:38.140 --> 00:45:41.260
So the Muslims and Abu Talib

00:45:41.260 --> 00:45:44.380
and some of the family members of Muhammad SAW,

00:45:44.380 --> 00:45:48.380
they used to ensure that he sleeps in a certain place

00:45:48.380 --> 00:45:51.220
where nobody would be able to reach him.

00:45:51.220 --> 00:45:53.740
So what they did, the people of Quraysh,

00:45:53.740 --> 00:45:55.060
they decided, right, you're staying there.

00:45:55.060 --> 00:45:56.820
You're not coming here.

00:45:56.820 --> 00:45:58.620
The Muslims were surrounded.

00:45:58.620 --> 00:46:00.540
They weren't allowed to come out.

00:46:00.540 --> 00:46:02.620
No one was allowed to go in with food,

00:46:02.620 --> 00:46:04.220
with any form of goodness.

00:46:04.220 --> 00:46:06.340
The one who was exempt from this,

00:46:06.340 --> 00:46:10.340
although he belonged to the family of Muhammad SAW,

00:46:10.340 --> 00:46:11.540
was Abu Lahab.

00:46:11.540 --> 00:46:13.020
Because he was an enemy.

00:46:13.020 --> 00:46:14.740
He was one of those who used to go around

00:46:14.740 --> 00:46:15.940
telling the people, watch out,

00:46:15.940 --> 00:46:17.740
don't even give them food.

00:46:17.740 --> 00:46:18.500
What happened?

00:46:18.500 --> 00:46:19.940
They had their provisions,

00:46:19.940 --> 00:46:21.940
their food depleted.

00:46:21.940 --> 00:46:24.740
When it depleted, one year passed.

00:46:24.740 --> 00:46:26.020
One year passed, what happened?

00:46:26.020 --> 00:46:27.180
Another year passed.

00:46:27.180 --> 00:46:28.180
There was no food.

00:46:28.180 --> 00:46:29.180
No one gave them food.

00:46:29.180 --> 00:46:30.140
No one dealt with them.

00:46:30.140 --> 00:46:31.260
Nothing happened.

00:46:31.260 --> 00:46:32.580
Wallahi.

00:46:32.580 --> 00:46:37.300
The Prophet SAW began to eat leaves of the tree

00:46:37.300 --> 00:46:39.500
together with his companions.

00:46:39.500 --> 00:46:42.100
And together with some

00:46:42.140 --> 00:46:43.660
who were not even Muslim,

00:46:43.660 --> 00:46:44.620
who happened to be there

00:46:44.620 --> 00:46:48.460
because it was their family, a few.

00:46:48.460 --> 00:46:51.020
And no one battered an island from Quraysh.

00:46:51.020 --> 00:46:52.820
They're watching these people suffering

00:46:52.820 --> 00:46:56.460
so much so that they began to cook the skins

00:46:56.460 --> 00:46:59.500
or roast the skins of the animals.

00:46:59.500 --> 00:47:02.340
They had eaten up all their animals.

00:47:02.340 --> 00:47:04.700
Roasting the skins of their animals

00:47:04.700 --> 00:47:08.860
and chewing on the inside of that skin,

00:47:08.860 --> 00:47:10.580
Allahu Akbar, to try and extract

00:47:10.580 --> 00:47:12.340
whatever goodness they could have had.

00:47:12.340 --> 00:47:15.580
And sucking on the roots of some of these shrubs

00:47:15.580 --> 00:47:17.220
that were there in the desert

00:47:17.220 --> 00:47:20.060
in order to get water.

00:47:20.060 --> 00:47:23.140
They had suffered for three years

00:47:23.140 --> 00:47:25.780
in what was known as Shi'a bi Abi Talib.

00:47:25.780 --> 00:47:28.380
The name of this place, like a valley,

00:47:28.380 --> 00:47:30.780
just in the outskirts of where these people were,

00:47:30.780 --> 00:47:32.780
where the Muslims were now surrounded.

00:47:32.780 --> 00:47:34.140
And what had happened?

00:47:34.140 --> 00:47:35.420
Allahu Akbar.

00:47:35.420 --> 00:47:38.500
Muhammad SAW allowed his companions,

00:47:38.500 --> 00:47:39.580
instructed them,

00:47:39.620 --> 00:47:41.140
you can now go to Habashah.

00:47:41.140 --> 00:47:42.420
Go back to Abyssinia.

00:47:42.420 --> 00:47:43.940
You can go back to Abyssinia.

00:47:43.940 --> 00:47:46.420
InshaAllah, Allah will grant you a place there.

00:47:46.420 --> 00:47:47.940
Allah will grant you safety.

00:47:47.940 --> 00:47:49.860
There is a ruler there who is just.

00:47:49.860 --> 00:47:51.380
He is an African ruler

00:47:51.380 --> 00:47:53.540
who is a Christian man who is just.

00:47:53.540 --> 00:47:54.940
He will not oppress you.

00:47:54.940 --> 00:47:57.660
He will treat you well and he will welcome you

00:47:57.660 --> 00:47:59.820
and he will look after you.

00:47:59.820 --> 00:48:01.500
His name is Ashamah.

00:48:01.500 --> 00:48:03.540
He is the Negus of Abyssinia,

00:48:03.540 --> 00:48:08.650
where Ethiopia is today.

00:48:08.650 --> 00:48:11.210
So it is reported that the second batch of people

00:48:11.250 --> 00:48:12.930
silently left.

00:48:12.930 --> 00:48:16.090
And this time, it was more difficult to leave.

00:48:16.090 --> 00:48:20.250
From amongst them, it is reported there were 83 men.

00:48:20.250 --> 00:48:22.490
If we count Ammar ibn Yasir, 83.

00:48:22.490 --> 00:48:24.130
And if we don't count him, 82.

00:48:24.130 --> 00:48:25.250
There is a difference of opinion

00:48:25.250 --> 00:48:28.010
as to whether he went or did not go.

00:48:28.010 --> 00:48:31.210
And 18 women, they had left.

00:48:32.290 --> 00:48:36.170
And the Amir or the person who was made their leader

00:48:36.170 --> 00:48:39.850
was Ja'far ibn Abi Talib r.a.

00:48:39.850 --> 00:48:40.890
And they had gone.

00:48:40.890 --> 00:48:42.130
They arrived in Abyssinia.

00:48:42.130 --> 00:48:43.930
Meanwhile, the Muslims are suffering

00:48:43.930 --> 00:48:47.250
in this sanctioned area

00:48:47.250 --> 00:48:49.370
where they were completely surrounded.

00:48:49.370 --> 00:48:50.730
Nothing goes in, nothing comes out.

00:48:50.730 --> 00:48:51.690
No one talks to them.

00:48:51.690 --> 00:48:54.750
Nothing happens.

00:48:54.750 --> 00:48:56.990
So when Ja'far ibn Abi Talib r.a.

00:48:56.990 --> 00:48:59.030
got with his group of men and women

00:48:59.030 --> 00:49:01.150
to Najashi in Africa,

00:49:01.150 --> 00:49:02.710
this was the first place

00:49:02.710 --> 00:49:05.270
that Islam got a base besides Arabia.

00:49:05.270 --> 00:49:06.270
Before Medina,

00:49:06.270 --> 00:49:08.190
already Islam had arrived in Africa.

00:49:08.190 --> 00:49:09.030
Subhanallah.

00:49:10.230 --> 00:49:11.950
Islam had arrived in Africa

00:49:11.950 --> 00:49:13.830
first before everywhere else.

00:49:15.070 --> 00:49:16.910
And this was just a few years in,

00:49:16.910 --> 00:49:20.630
approximately five years after the prophethood.

00:49:20.630 --> 00:49:22.310
Five years after the prophethood,

00:49:22.310 --> 00:49:23.990
it already arrived in Africa.

00:49:23.990 --> 00:49:26.230
And Ja'far ibn Abi Talib r.a.

00:49:26.230 --> 00:49:27.430
tells Najashi,

00:49:27.430 --> 00:49:29.190
we are people, we've been oppressed.

00:49:29.190 --> 00:49:32.510
We have a Nabi amongst us,

00:49:32.510 --> 00:49:34.990
a messenger who has come with the word of Allah.

00:49:34.990 --> 00:49:37.230
He has instructed us to do this, to do that,

00:49:37.230 --> 00:49:38.870
to stop worshiping idols,

00:49:38.870 --> 00:49:40.430
to stop oppressing our women,

00:49:40.430 --> 00:49:41.870
to stop cheating and deceiving,

00:49:41.870 --> 00:49:43.070
to look after our neighbors,

00:49:43.070 --> 00:49:44.790
to honor our treaties

00:49:44.790 --> 00:49:46.550
and to fulfill our promises.

00:49:46.550 --> 00:49:48.750
And he has instructed us to pray

00:49:48.750 --> 00:49:51.950
and to fast and to give alms to the poor and so on.

00:49:51.950 --> 00:49:54.310
And he has done this and that.

00:49:54.310 --> 00:49:56.590
And our people began to persecute us.

00:49:56.590 --> 00:49:57.790
They wanted us to go back

00:49:57.790 --> 00:49:59.470
to the religion of our forefathers.

00:49:59.470 --> 00:50:00.350
They want us.

00:50:00.350 --> 00:50:03.470
We were a nation who used to bury our daughters alive.

00:50:03.470 --> 00:50:05.270
We were a nation who used to engage

00:50:05.270 --> 00:50:07.630
in so much mockery of our own women folk.

00:50:07.630 --> 00:50:10.390
We used to buy and sell and trade in human beings.

00:50:10.390 --> 00:50:11.710
And we used to do this and that.

00:50:11.710 --> 00:50:12.790
And so many different things.

00:50:12.790 --> 00:50:15.070
And we used to worship idols completely

00:50:15.070 --> 00:50:17.830
until Allah sent in our midst a messenger

00:50:17.830 --> 00:50:19.030
who came with a book.

00:50:19.030 --> 00:50:20.910
And he came with a revelation.

00:50:20.910 --> 00:50:21.750
Revelation.

00:50:23.190 --> 00:50:25.230
And he instructed us to do this and this.

00:50:25.230 --> 00:50:26.430
Najashi heard.

00:50:26.430 --> 00:50:27.270
And he told him,

00:50:27.270 --> 00:50:28.750
you are welcome in this land

00:50:28.750 --> 00:50:31.150
and you will be protected here

00:50:31.150 --> 00:50:33.190
and you may worship Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:50:33.190 --> 00:50:34.910
But hang on.

00:50:34.910 --> 00:50:36.910
The people of Quraysh,

00:50:36.910 --> 00:50:38.790
they had already sent their men,

00:50:38.790 --> 00:50:40.310
Amr ibn al-As.

00:50:40.350 --> 00:50:43.390
He was sent with Abdullah ibn Abi Rabiah.

00:50:44.470 --> 00:50:46.590
And some narrations make mention of

00:50:48.750 --> 00:50:50.630
Amr ibn al-Waleed.

00:50:50.630 --> 00:50:52.710
They were sent to Najashi as well.

00:50:52.710 --> 00:50:54.070
They got to Najashi.

00:50:54.070 --> 00:50:57.110
They said, wait, these people are traitors.

00:50:57.110 --> 00:51:00.550
We are here in order to get back certain young people

00:51:00.550 --> 00:51:01.950
who have ran away

00:51:01.950 --> 00:51:05.110
and they are being sought after in Quraysh.

00:51:05.110 --> 00:51:07.110
And our people have sent us here.

00:51:07.110 --> 00:51:09.470
And we come here to trade a lot.

00:51:09.470 --> 00:51:11.310
And we need these people back

00:51:11.310 --> 00:51:13.350
because they have been swearing our gods

00:51:13.350 --> 00:51:14.350
and they have turned away

00:51:14.350 --> 00:51:15.870
from the religion of our forefathers

00:51:15.870 --> 00:51:17.230
and, and, and.

00:51:17.230 --> 00:51:19.190
And Najashi was so upset.

00:51:19.190 --> 00:51:20.070
So upset.

00:51:20.070 --> 00:51:21.150
Very angry.

00:51:21.150 --> 00:51:22.470
Because they had brought him gifts.

00:51:22.470 --> 00:51:23.590
They gave him lots of gifts.

00:51:23.590 --> 00:51:25.150
They were wealthy people, Quraysh.

00:51:25.150 --> 00:51:26.790
They brought him gifts and so on.

00:51:26.790 --> 00:51:28.870
And he heard from Ja'far ibn Abi Talib.

00:51:30.390 --> 00:51:31.830
And he says,

00:51:31.830 --> 00:51:33.070
these people are correct.

00:51:33.070 --> 00:51:34.910
They will stay here

00:51:34.910 --> 00:51:37.470
and you will not be able to do anything.

00:51:37.470 --> 00:51:38.310
You need to return.

00:51:38.310 --> 00:51:39.150
The following morning,

00:51:39.150 --> 00:51:40.310
these two decided,

00:51:40.310 --> 00:51:42.830
let's try and strike a chord.

00:51:44.150 --> 00:51:46.110
So they go to Najashi in the morning

00:51:46.110 --> 00:51:47.390
and they say,

00:51:47.390 --> 00:51:48.950
you know what they say about Jesus?

00:51:48.950 --> 00:51:50.510
May peace be upon him.

00:51:50.510 --> 00:51:51.350
Isa.

00:51:51.350 --> 00:51:52.390
They know this man is a Christian.

00:51:52.390 --> 00:51:53.270
So they say,

00:51:53.270 --> 00:51:55.550
these people blaspheme Jesus.

00:51:55.550 --> 00:51:57.510
So Najashi calls Ja'far ibn Abi Talib.

00:51:57.510 --> 00:51:58.270
He says,

00:51:58.270 --> 00:51:59.670
what do you say about Jesus?

00:51:59.670 --> 00:52:00.670
He says,

00:52:01.910 --> 00:52:04.630
we say whatever Allah has instructed us.

00:52:05.630 --> 00:52:07.710
Whatever our messenger has instructed us.

00:52:07.710 --> 00:52:11.390
We say that he was

00:52:11.390 --> 00:52:14.110
the miracle of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:52:14.110 --> 00:52:16.870
granted to the Virgin Mary.

00:52:16.870 --> 00:52:20.110
And he was born without a father.

00:52:20.110 --> 00:52:24.230
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala gave him life.

00:52:24.230 --> 00:52:27.110
He spoke to people when he was a baby.

00:52:27.110 --> 00:52:30.750
And he declared that he is Abdullah wa Rasuluhu.

00:52:30.750 --> 00:52:32.510
He is none other than a messenger

00:52:32.510 --> 00:52:34.190
of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:52:34.190 --> 00:52:35.390
and the prophet of his.

00:52:35.390 --> 00:52:36.390
And that's what we say.

00:52:36.390 --> 00:52:37.870
And we stop there.

00:52:37.870 --> 00:52:40.310
So Najashi looks and he says,

00:52:40.310 --> 00:52:42.190
read me some verses

00:52:42.190 --> 00:52:43.670
from what you have.

00:52:45.150 --> 00:52:46.590
So they started reading the verses

00:52:46.590 --> 00:52:48.310
Kaaf Ha Ya Ain Saal.

00:52:48.310 --> 00:52:49.150
Allahu Akbar.

00:52:50.190 --> 00:52:55.190
Dhikru rahmati rabbika abdahu zakariya

00:52:55.190 --> 00:53:00.190
Ith naada rabbahu nida'an khafiyya

00:53:01.350 --> 00:53:03.830
Najashi, just like Omar ibn Al-Khattab

00:53:03.830 --> 00:53:06.030
radiallahu anhu began to cry.

00:53:06.070 --> 00:53:08.430
So much so that verses were revealed

00:53:08.430 --> 00:53:11.270
telling Muhammad Sallallahu Alaihi Wasallam

00:53:11.270 --> 00:53:12.950
that they are people

00:53:12.950 --> 00:53:15.070
who are leaders of the Christians

00:53:15.070 --> 00:53:16.750
whom when they heard the Quran,

00:53:16.750 --> 00:53:18.190
they began to weep.

00:53:18.190 --> 00:53:23.190
Wa ida sami'u ma'unzil ila al-rasul

00:53:24.670 --> 00:53:29.670
Tara a'iyunahum tafeedu min al-dam'i

00:53:29.670 --> 00:53:33.190
Mimma arafu min al-haqqu

00:53:33.190 --> 00:53:37.870
Yaquluna rabbana amanna

00:53:37.870 --> 00:53:41.790
Fakhtubna ma'ashshahideen

00:53:41.790 --> 00:53:44.070
When they heard the verses of the Quran

00:53:44.070 --> 00:53:47.390
being read, their eyes became filled with tears.

00:53:47.390 --> 00:53:49.430
The tears began to roll down

00:53:49.430 --> 00:53:51.470
because of what they knew was the truth.

00:53:51.470 --> 00:53:53.350
And they said, oh our Rabb, we believe.

00:53:53.350 --> 00:53:55.390
So write us from amongst those

00:53:55.390 --> 00:53:56.750
who have borne witness.

00:53:56.750 --> 00:53:58.310
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:53:58.310 --> 00:53:59.470
to grant us goodness.

00:53:59.470 --> 00:54:01.550
Insha'Allah, tomorrow we will go through

00:54:01.590 --> 00:54:03.830
what happened at this particular time

00:54:03.830 --> 00:54:05.590
with Ja'far ibn Abi Talib

00:54:05.590 --> 00:54:08.230
and with Amr ibn al-Aas radiallahu anhu.

00:54:08.230 --> 00:54:10.510
And by the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:54:10.510 --> 00:54:13.110
we will get to see the victory of the Muslims

00:54:13.110 --> 00:54:14.110
and what had happened.

00:54:14.110 --> 00:54:16.150
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:54:16.150 --> 00:54:17.230
until we meet again.

00:54:17.230 --> 00:54:20.790
Wa salallahu wa sallam wa baraka ala nabina Muhammad.

00:54:20.790 --> 00:54:24.550
As-salamu alaikum wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuh.

00:54:24.550 --> 00:54:29.790
Alif Laam Mim

00:54:29.790 --> 00:54:33.830
Allah, la ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hijj Al-Qayyum.
